  26,14,"Also, they have a charge against me,¬†so I fear they may kill me.‚ÄĚ"
  26,15,"God responded, ‚ÄúCertainly not! So go, both of you, with Our signs. We will be with you, listening"
  26,16,"Go to Pharaoh and say, ‚ÄėWe are messengers from the Lord of all worlds"
  26,17,"ňĻcommanded to say:ňļ ‚ÄėLet the Children of Israel go with us.‚Äô‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  26,18,"Pharaoh protested, ‚ÄúDid we not raise you among us as a child, and you stayed several years of your life in our care"
  26,19,"Then you did what you did,¬†being ňĻutterlyňļ ungrateful!‚ÄĚ"
  26,20,"Moses replied, ‚ÄúI did it then, lacking guidance"
