  26,59,So it was. And We awarded it ňĻallňļ to the Children of Israel
  26,60,And so they pursued them at sunrise
  26,61,"When the two groups came face to face, the companions of Moses cried out, ‚ÄúWe are overtaken for sure.‚ÄĚ"
  26,62,"Moses reassured ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúAbsolutely not! My Lord is certainly with me‚ÄĒHe will guide me.‚ÄĚ"
  26,63,"So We inspired Moses: ‚ÄúStrike the sea with your staff,‚ÄĚ and the sea was split, each part was like a huge mountain"
