  26,74,"They replied, ‚ÄúNo! But we found our forefathers doing the same.‚ÄĚ"
  26,75,"Abraham responded, ‚ÄúHave you ňĻreallyňļ considered what you have been worshipping‚ÄĒ"
  26,76,you and your ancestors
  26,77,"They are ňĻallňļ enemies to me, except the Lord of all worlds"
  26,78,"ňĻHe isňļ the One Who created me, and He ňĻaloneňļ guides me"
  26,79,ňĻHe isňļ the One Who provides me with food and drink
  26,80,And He ňĻaloneňļ heals me when I am sick
  26,81,"And He ňĻis the One Whoňļ will cause me to die, and then bring me back to life"
  26,82,"And He is ňĻthe Oneňļ Who, I hope, will forgive my flaws¬†on Judgment Day.‚ÄĚ"
  26,83,"‚ÄúMy Lord! Grant me wisdom, and join me with the righteous"
  26,84,Bless me with honourable mention among later generations
  26,85,Make me one of those awarded the Garden of Bliss
  26,86,"Forgive my father, for he is certainly one of the misguided"
  26,87,And do not disgrace me on the Day all will be resurrected‚ÄĒ
  26,88,the Day when neither wealth nor children will be of any benefit
  26,89,Only those who come before God with a pure heart ňĻwill be savedňļ.‚ÄĚ
  26,90,ňĻOn that Dayňļ Paradise will be brought near to the God-fearing
  26,91,and the Hellfire will be displayed to the deviant
  26,92,"And it will be said to them, ‚ÄúWhere are those you used to worship"
  26,93,besides God? Can they help you or even help themselves?‚ÄĚ
  26,94,"Then the idols will be hurled headlong into Hell, along with the deviant"
  26,95,"and the soldiers of Ibl√ģs,¬†all together"
  26,96,There the deviant will cry while disputing with their idols
  26,97,‚ÄúBy God! We were clearly mistaken
  26,98,when we made you equal to the Lord of all worlds
  26,99,And none led us astray other than the wicked
  26,100,Now we have none to intercede for us
  26,101,nor a close friend
  26,102,"If only we could have a second chance, then we would be believers.‚ÄĚ"
  26,103,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,104,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,105,The people of Noah rejected the messengers
  26,106,"when their brother Noah said to them, ‚ÄúWill you not fear ňĻGodňļ"
  26,107,I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,108,"So fear God, and obey me"
  26,109,I do not ask you for any reward for this ňĻmessageňļ. My reward is only from the Lord of all worlds
  26,110,"So fear God, and obey me.‚ÄĚ"
  26,111,"They argued, ‚ÄúHow can we believe in you, when you are followed ňĻonlyňļ by the lowest of the low?‚ÄĚ"
  26,112,"He responded, ‚ÄúAnd what knowledge do I have of what they do"
  26,113,"Their judgment is with my Lord, if you had any sense"
  26,114,I am not going to expel the believers
  26,115,I am only sent with a clear warning.‚ÄĚ
  26,116,"They threatened, ‚ÄúIf you do not desist, O Noah, you will surely be stoned ňĻto deathňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  26,117,"Noah prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! My people have truly rejected me"
  26,118,"So judge between me and them decisively, and save me and the believers with me.‚ÄĚ"
  26,119,So We saved him and those with him in the fully loaded Ark
  26,120,Then afterwards We drowned the rest
  26,121,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,122,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,123,The people of ‚Äô√ād rejected the messengers
  26,124,"when their brother H√Ľd said to them, ‚ÄúWill you not fear ňĻGodňļ"
  26,125,I am truly a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,126,"So fear God, and obey me"
  26,127,I do not ask you for any reward for this ňĻmessageňļ. My reward is only from the Lord of all worlds
  26,128,ňĻWhyňļ do you build a landmark on every high place in vanity
  26,129,"and construct castles, as if you are going to live forever"
  26,130,and act so viciously when you attack ňĻothersňļ
