  26,222,They descend upon every sinful liar
  26,223,"who gives an ňĻattentiveňļ ear ňĻto half-truthsňļ, mostly passing on sheer lies"
  26,224,"As for poets, they are followed ňĻmerelyňļ by deviants"
  26,225,Do you not see how they rant in every field
  26,226,only saying what they never do
  26,227,"Except those who believe, do good, remember God often, and ňĻpoeticallyňļ avenge ňĻthe believersňļ after being wrongfully slandered. The wrongdoers will come to know what ňĻevilňļ end they will meet"
  27,1,ŠĻ¨√Ę-Sń©n. These are the verses of the Quran; the clear Book
  27,2,ňĻIt isňļ a guide and good news for the believers
  27,3,"ňĻthoseňļ who establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  27,4,"As for those who do not believe in the Hereafter, We have certainly made their ňĻevilňļ deeds appealing to them, so they wander blindly"
  27,5,"It is they who will suffer a dreadful torment, and in the Hereafter they will ňĻtrulyňļ be the greatest losers"
  27,6,"And indeed, you ňĻO Prophetňļ are receiving the Quran from the One ňĻWho isňļ All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  27,7,"ňĻRememberňļ when Moses said to his family, ‚ÄúI have spotted a fire. I will either bring you some directions¬†from there, or a burning torch so you may warm yourselves.‚ÄĚ"
  27,8,"But when he came to it, he was called ňĻby Godňļ, ‚ÄúBlessed is the one at the fire, and whoever is around it!¬†Glory be to God, the Lord of all worlds"
  27,9,"O Moses! It is truly I. I am God‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  27,10,"Now, throw down your staff!‚ÄĚ But when he saw it slithering like a snake, he ran away without looking back. ňĻGod reassured him,ňļ ‚ÄúO Moses! Do not be afraid! Messengers should have no fear in My presence"
  27,11,"ňĻFear isňļ only for those who do wrong. But if they later mend ňĻtheirňļ evil ňĻwaysňļ with good, then I am certainly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  27,12,"Now put your hand through ňĻthe opening ofňļ your collar, it will come out ňĻshiningňļ white, unblemished.¬†ňĻThese are twoňļ of nine signs for Pharaoh and his people.¬†They have truly been a rebellious people.‚ÄĚ"
  27,13,"But when Our enlightening signs came to them, they said, ‚ÄúThis is pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  27,14,"And, although their hearts were convinced the signs were true, they still denied them wrongfully and arrogantly. See then what was the end of the corruptors"
  27,15,"Indeed, We granted knowledge to David and Solomon. And they said ňĻin acknowledgmentňļ, ‚ÄúAll praise is for God Who has privileged us over many of His faithful servants.‚ÄĚ"
  27,16,"And David was succeeded by Solomon, who said, ‚ÄúO people! We have been taught the language of birds, and been given everything ňĻwe needňļ. This is indeed a great privilege.‚ÄĚ"
  27,17,"Solomon‚Äôs forces of jinn, humans, and birds were rallied for him, perfectly organized"
  27,18,"And when they came across a valley of ants, an ant warned, ‚ÄúO ants! Go quickly into your homes so Solomon and his armies do not crush you, unknowingly.‚ÄĚ"
  27,19,"So Solomon smiled in amusement at her words, and prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Inspire me to ňĻalwaysňļ be thankful for Your favours which You have blessed me and my parents with, and to do good deeds that please you. Admit me, by Your mercy, into ňĻthe company ofňļ Your righteous servants.‚ÄĚ"
  27,20,"ňĻOne dayňļ he inspected the birds, and wondered, ‚ÄúWhy is it that I cannot see the hoopoe? Or could he be absent"
  27,21,"I will surely subject him to a severe punishment, or ňĻevenňļ slaughter him, unless he brings me a compelling excuse.‚ÄĚ"
  27,22,"It was not long before the bird came and said, ‚ÄúI have found out something you do not know. I have just come to you from Sheba with sure news"
  27,23,"Indeed, I found a woman ruling over them,¬†who has been given everything ňĻshe needsňļ, and who has a magnificent throne"
  27,24,I found her and her people prostrating to the sun instead of God. For Satan has made their deeds appealing to them‚ÄĒhindering them from the ňĻRightňļ Way and leaving them unguided‚ÄĒ
  27,25,"so they do not prostrate to God, Who brings forth what is hidden in the heavens and the earth, and knows what you ňĻallňļ conceal and what you reveal"
  27,26,"ňĻHe isňļ God! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him, the Lord of the Mighty Throne.‚ÄĚ"
  27,27,"Solomon said, ‚ÄúWe will see whether you are telling the truth or lying"
  27,28,"Go with this letter of mine and deliver it to them, then stand aside and see how they will respond.‚ÄĚ"
  27,29,"The Queen ňĻlaterňļ announced, ‚ÄúO chiefs! Indeed, a noble letter has been delivered to me"
  27,30,"It is from Solomon, and it reads: ‚ÄėIn the Name of God‚ÄĒthe Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  27,31,"Do not be arrogant with me, but come to me, fully submitting ňĻto Godňļ.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  27,32,"She said, ‚ÄúO chiefs! Advise me in this matter of mine, for I would never make any decision without you.‚ÄĚ"
  27,33,"They responded, ‚ÄúWe are a people of strength and great ňĻmilitaryňļ might, but the decision is yours, so decide what you will command.‚ÄĚ"
  27,34,"She reasoned, ‚ÄúIndeed, when kings invade a land, they ruin it and debase its nobles. They really do so"
  27,35,"But I will certainly send him a gift, and see what ňĻresponseňļ my envoys will return with.‚ÄĚ"
  27,36,"When the chief-envoy came to him, Solomon said, ‚ÄúDo you offer me wealth? What God has granted me is far greater than what He has granted you. No! It is you who rejoice in ňĻreceivingňļ gifts"
  27,37,"Go back to them, for we will certainly mobilize against them forces which they can never resist, and we will drive them out from there in disgrace, fully humbled.‚ÄĚ"
  27,38,"Solomon asked, ‚ÄúO chiefs! Which of you can bring me her throne before they come to me in ňĻfullňļ submission?‚ÄĚ"
  27,39,"One mighty jinn responded, ‚ÄúI can bring it to you before you rise from this council of yours. And I am quite strong and trustworthy for this ňĻtaskňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  27,40,"But the one who had knowledge of the Scripture said,¬†‚ÄúI can bring it to you in the blink of an eye.‚ÄĚ So when Solomon saw it placed before him, he exclaimed, ‚ÄúThis is by the grace of my Lord to test me whether I am grateful or ungrateful. And whoever is grateful, it is only for their own good. But whoever is ungrateful, surely my Lord is Self-Sufficient, Most Generous.‚ÄĚ"
  27,41,"ňĻThenňļ Solomon said, ‚ÄúDisguise her throne for her so we may see whether she will recognize ňĻitňļ or she will not be able to.‚ÄĚ"
  27,42,"So when she arrived, it was said ňĻto herňļ, ‚ÄúIs your throne like this?‚ÄĚ She replied, ‚ÄúIt looks to be the same. We have ňĻalreadyňļ received knowledge ňĻof Solomon‚Äôs prophethoodňļ¬†before this ňĻmiracleňļ,¬†and have submitted ňĻto Godňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  27,43,"But she had been hindered by what she used to worship instead of God, for she was indeed from a disbelieving people"
  27,44,"Then she was told, ‚ÄúEnter the palace.‚ÄĚ But when she saw the hall, she thought it was a body of water, so she bared her legs. Solomon said. ‚ÄúIt is just a palace paved with crystal.‚ÄĚ ňĻAt lastňļ she declared, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I have certainly wronged my soul. Now I ňĻfullyňļ submit myself along with Solomon to God, the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  27,45,"And We certainly sent to the people of Tham√Ľd their brother ŠĻĘ√ĘliŠł•, proclaiming, ‚ÄúWorship God,‚ÄĚ but they suddenly split into two opposing groups"
  27,46,"He urged ňĻthe disbelieving groupňļ, ‚ÄúO my people! Why do you ňĻseek toňļ hasten the torment¬†rather than grace?¬†If only you sought God‚Äôs forgiveness so you may be shown mercy!‚ÄĚ"
  27,47,"They replied, ‚ÄúYou and your followers are a bad omen for us.‚ÄĚ¬†He responded, ‚ÄúYour omens are destined by God. In fact, you are ňĻonlyňļ a people being tested.‚ÄĚ"
  27,48,"And there were in the city nine ňĻeliteňļ men who spread corruption in the land, never doing what is right"
  27,49,"They vowed, ‚ÄúLet us swear by God that we will take him and his family down by night. Then we will certainly say to his ňĻclosestňļ heirs, ‚ÄėWe did not witness the murder of his family. We are definitely telling the truth.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  27,50,"And ňĻsoňļ they made a plan, but We too made a plan, while they were unaware"
  27,51,"See then what the consequences of their plan were: We ňĻutterlyňļ destroyed them and their people all together"
  27,52,"So their homes are there, ňĻbut completelyňļ ruined because of their wrongdoing. Surely in this is a lesson for people of knowledge"
  27,53,And We delivered those who were faithful and were mindful ňĻof Godňļ
  27,54,"And ňĻrememberňļ Lot, when he rebuked ňĻthe men ofňļ his people, ‚ÄúDo you commit that shameful deed while you can see ňĻone anotherňļ"
  27,55,"Do you really lust after men instead of women? In fact, you are ňĻonlyňļ a people acting ignorantly.‚ÄĚ"
  27,56,"But his people‚Äôs only response was to say, ‚ÄúExpel Lot‚Äôs followers from your land! They are a people who wish to remain chaste!‚ÄĚ"
  27,57,"So We delivered him and his family, except his wife. We had destined her to be one of the doomed"
  27,58,And We poured upon them a rain ňĻof brimstoneňļ. How evil was the rain of those who had been warned
  27,59,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúPraise be to God, and peace be upon the servants He has chosen.‚ÄĚ ňĻAsk the disbelievers,ňļ ‚ÄúWhich is better: God or whatever ňĻgodsňļ they associate ňĻwith Himňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  27,60,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho created the heavens and the earth, and sends down rain for you from the sky, by which We cause delightful gardens to grow? You could never cause their trees to grow. Was it another god besides God?‚ÄĚ Absolutely not! But they are a people who set up equals ňĻto Godňļ"
  27,61,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho made the earth a place of settlement, caused rivers to flow through it, placed firm mountains upon it, and set a barrier between ňĻfresh and saltňļ bodies of water?¬†Was it another god besides God?‚ÄĚ Absolutely not! But most of them do not know"
  27,62,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho responds to the distressed when they cry to Him, relieving ňĻtheirňļ affliction, and ňĻWhoňļ makes you successors in the earth? Is it another god besides God? Yet you are hardly mindful!‚ÄĚ"
  27,63,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho guides you in the darkness of the land and sea,¬†and sends the winds ushering in His mercy?¬†Is it another god besides God? Exalted is God above what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ"
  27,64,"Or ňĻask them,ňļ ‚ÄúWho originates the creation then resurrects it, and gives you provisions from the heavens and the earth? Is it another god besides God?‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúShow ňĻmeňļ your proof, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  27,65,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúNone in the heavens and the earth has knowledge of the unseen except God. Nor do they know when they will be resurrected"
  27,66,"No! Their knowledge of the Hereafter amounts to ignorance. In fact, they are in doubt about it. In truth, they are ňĻtotallyňļ blind to it"
  27,67,"The disbelievers ask, ‚ÄúWhen we and our fathers are reduced to dust, will we really be brought forth ňĻaliveňļ"
  27,68,"We have already been promised this, as well as our forefathers earlier. This is nothing but ancient fables!‚ÄĚ"
  27,69,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúTravel throughout the land and see the fate of the wicked.‚ÄĚ"
  27,70,"Do not grieve for them, nor be distressed by their schemes"
  27,71,"They ask ňĻthe believersňļ, ‚ÄúWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  27,72,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúPerhaps some of what you seek to hasten is close at hand.‚ÄĚ"
  27,73,"Surely your Lord is ever Bountiful to humanity,¬†but most of them are ungrateful"
  27,74,And surely your Lord knows what their hearts conceal and what they reveal
  27,75,For there is nothing hidden in the heavens or the earth without being ňĻwrittenňļ in a perfect Record
  27,76,"Indeed, this Quran clarifies for the Children of Israel most of what they differ over"
  27,77,And it is truly a guide and mercy for the believers
  27,78,"Your Lord will certainly judge between them by His justice, for He is the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  27,79,"So put your trust in God, for you are surely upon the ňĻPath ofňļ clear truth"
  27,80,You certainly cannot make the dead hear ňĻthe truthňļ. Nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and walk away
  27,81,"Nor can you lead the blind out of their misguidance. You can make none hear ňĻthe truthňļ except those who believe in Our revelations, ňĻfullyňļ submitting ňĻto Godňļ"
  27,82,"And when the decree ňĻof the Hourňļ comes to pass against them, We will bring forth for them a beast from the earth,¬†telling them that the people had no sure faith in Our revelations"
  27,83,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day We will gather from every faith-community a group of those who denied Our revelations, and they will be driven in ranks"
  27,84,"When they ňĻfinallyňļ come before their Lord, He will ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúDid you deny My revelations without ňĻevenňļ comprehending them? Or what ňĻexactlyňļ did you do?‚ÄĚ"
  27,85,"And the decree ňĻof tormentňļ will be justified against them for their wrongdoing, leaving them speechless"
  27,86,Do they not see that We made the night for them to rest in and the day bright?¬†Surely in this are signs for those who believe
  27,87,"And ňĻbeware ofňļ the Day the Trumpet will be blown, and all those in the heavens and all those on the earth will be horrified ňĻto the point of deathňļ,¬†except those God wills ňĻto spareňļ. And all will come before Him, fully humbled"
  27,88,"Now you see the mountains, thinking they are firmly fixed, but they are travelling ňĻjustňļ like clouds. ňĻThat isňļ the design of God, Who has perfected everything. Surely He is All-Aware of what you do"
  27,89,"Whoever comes with a good deed will be rewarded with what is better, and they will be secure from the horror on that Day"
  27,90,And whoever comes with an evil deed will be hurled face-first into the Fire. Are you rewarded except for what you used to do
  27,91,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI have only been commanded to worship the Lord of this city ňĻof Meccaňļ, Who has made it sacred, and to Him belongs everything. And I am commanded to be one of those who ňĻfullyňļ submit ňĻto Himňļ"
  27,92,"and to recite the Quran.‚ÄĚ Then whoever chooses to be guided, it is only for their own good. But whoever chooses to stray, say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI am only a warner.‚ÄĚ"
  27,93,"And say, ‚ÄúAll praise is for God! He will show you His signs, and you will recognize them. And your Lord is never unaware of what you do.‚ÄĚ"
  28,1,ŠĻ¨√Ę-Sń©n-Mń©m
  28,2,These are the verses of the clear Book
  28,3,We narrate to you ňĻO Prophetňļ part of the story of Moses and Pharaoh in truth for people who believe
  28,4,"Indeed, Pharaoh ňĻarrogantlyňļ elevated himself in the land and divided its people into ňĻsubservientňļ groups, one of which he persecuted, slaughtering their sons and keeping their women. He was truly one of the corruptors"
  28,5,"But it was Our Will to favour those who were oppressed in the land, making them models ňĻof faithňļ as well as successors"
  28,6,"and to establish them in the land; and through them show Pharaoh, Ham√Ęn,¬†and their soldiers ňĻthe fulfilment ofňļ what they feared"
  28,7,"We inspired the mother of Moses: ‚ÄúNurse him, but when you fear for him, put him then into the river, and do not fear or grieve. We will certainly return him to you, and make him one of the messengers.‚ÄĚ"
  28,8,"And ňĻit so happened thatňļ Pharaoh‚Äôs people picked him up, only to become their enemy and source of grief. Surely Pharaoh, Ham√Ęn, and their soldiers were sinful"
  28,9,"Pharaoh‚Äôs wife said ňĻto himňļ, ‚ÄúňĻThis baby isňļ a source of joy for me and you. Do not kill him. Perhaps he may be useful to us or we may adopt him as a son.‚ÄĚ They were unaware ňĻof what was to comeňļ"
  28,10,"And the heart of Moses‚Äô mother ached so much that she almost gave away his identity, had We not reassured her heart in order for her to have faith ňĻin God‚Äôs promiseňļ"
  28,11,"And she said to his sister, ‚ÄúKeep track of him!‚ÄĚ So she watched him from a distance, while they were unaware"
  28,12,"And We had caused him to refuse all wet-nurses at first, so his sister suggested, ‚ÄúShall I direct you to a family who will bring him up for you and take good care of him?‚ÄĚ"
  28,13,"This is how We returned him to his mother so that her heart would be put at ease, and not grieve, and that she would know that God‚Äôs promise is ňĻalwaysňļ true. But most people do not know"
  28,14,"And when he reached full strength and maturity, We gave him wisdom and knowledge. This is how We reward the good-doers"
  28,15,"ňĻOne dayňļ he entered the city unnoticed by its people.¬†There he found two men fighting: one of his own people, and the other of his enemies. The man from his people called to him for help against his foe. So Moses punched him, causing his death. Moses cried, ‚ÄúThis is from Satan‚Äôs handiwork. He is certainly a sworn, misleading enemy.‚ÄĚ"
  28,16,"He pleaded, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I have definitely wronged my soul, so forgive me.‚ÄĚ So He forgave him, ňĻforňļ He is indeed the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  28,17,"Moses pledged, ‚ÄúMy Lord! For all Your favours upon me, I will never side with the wicked.‚ÄĚ"
  28,18,"And so Moses became fearful, watching out in the city, when suddenly the one who sought his help the day before cried out to him again for help. Moses rebuked him, ‚ÄúIndeed, you are clearly a trouble-maker.‚ÄĚ"
  28,19,"Then when Moses was about to lay his hands on their foe,¬†the enemy said, ‚ÄúO Moses! Do you intend to kill me as you killed a man yesterday? You only want to be a tyrant in the land. You do not intend to make peace!‚ÄĚ"
  28,20,"And there came a man, rushing from the farthest end of the city. He said, ‚ÄúO Moses! The chiefs are actually conspiring against you to put you to death, so leave ňĻthe cityňļ. I really advise you ňĻto do soňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  28,21,"So Moses left the city in a state of fear and caution, praying, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Deliver me from the wrongdoing people.‚ÄĚ"
  28,22,"And as he made his way towards Midian, he said, ‚ÄúI trust my Lord will guide me to the right way.‚ÄĚ"
  28,23,"When he arrived at the well of Midian, he found a group of people watering ňĻtheir herdsňļ. Apart from them, he noticed two women holding back ňĻtheir herdňļ. He asked ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúWhat is the problem?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúWe cannot water ňĻour animalsňļ until the ňĻotherňļ shepherds are done, for our father is a very old man.‚ÄĚ"
  28,24,"So he watered ňĻtheir herdňļ for them, then withdrew to the shade and prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I am truly in ňĻdesperateňļ need of whatever provision You may have in store for me.‚ÄĚ"
  28,25,"Then one of the two women came to him, walking bashfully. She said, ‚ÄúMy father is inviting you so he may reward you for watering ňĻour animalsňļ for us.‚ÄĚ When Moses came to him and told him his whole story, the old man said, ‚ÄúHave no fear! You are ňĻnowňļ safe from the wrongdoing people.‚ÄĚ"
  28,26,"One of the two daughters suggested, ‚ÄúO my dear father! Hire him. The best man for employment is definitely the strong and trustworthy ňĻoneňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  28,27,"The old man proposed, ‚ÄúI wish to marry one of these two daughters of mine to you, provided that you stay in my service for eight years. If you complete ten, it will be ňĻa favourňļ from you, but I do not wish to make it difficult for you. God willing, you will find me an agreeable man.‚ÄĚ"
  28,28,"Moses responded, ‚ÄúňĻThenňļ it is ňĻsettledňļ between you and I. Whichever term I fulfill, there will be no ňĻfurtherňļ obligation on me. And God is a Witness to what we say.‚ÄĚ"
  28,29,"When Moses had completed the term and was travelling with his family, he spotted a fire on the side of Mount ŠĻ¨√Ľr. He said to his family, ‚ÄúStay here, ňĻforňļ I have spotted a fire. Perhaps from there I can bring you some directions¬†or a torch from the fire so you may warm yourselves.‚ÄĚ"
  28,30,"But when he came to it, he was called from the bush in the sacred ground to the right side of the valley: ‚ÄúO Moses! It is truly I. I am God‚ÄĒthe Lord of all worlds"
  28,31,"Now, throw down your staff!‚ÄĚ But when he saw it slithering like a snake, he ran away without looking back. ňĻGod reassured him,ňļ ‚ÄúO Moses! Draw near, and have no fear. You are perfectly secure"
  28,32,"Now put your hand through ňĻthe opening ofňļ your collar, it will come out ňĻshiningňļ white, unblemished.¬†And cross your arms tightly to calm your fears.¬†These are two proofs from your Lord to Pharaoh and his chiefs. They have truly been a rebellious people.‚ÄĚ"
  28,33,"Moses appealed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I have indeed killed a man from them, so I fear they may kill me"
  28,34,"And my brother Aaron is more eloquent than I, so send him with me as a helper to support what I say, for I truly fear they may reject me.‚ÄĚ"
  28,35,"God responded, ‚ÄúWe will assist you with your brother and grant you both authority, so they cannot harm you. With Our signs, you and those who follow you will ňĻcertainlyňļ prevail.‚ÄĚ"
  28,36,"But when Moses came to them with Our clear signs, they said ňĻarrogantlyňļ, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but conjured magic ňĻtricksňļ. We have never heard of this in ňĻthe history ofňļ our forefathers.‚ÄĚ"
  28,37,"Moses responded, ‚ÄúMy Lord knows best who has come with ňĻtrueňļ guidance from Him and will fare best in the end. Indeed, the wrongdoers will never succeed.‚ÄĚ"
  28,38,"Pharaoh declared, ‚ÄúO chiefs! I know of no other god for you but myself. So bake bricks out of clay for me, O Ham√Ęn, and build a high tower so I may look at the God of Moses, although I am sure he is a liar.‚ÄĚ"
  28,39,"And so he and his soldiers behaved arrogantly in the land with no right, thinking they would never be returned to Us"
  28,40,"So We seized him and his soldiers, casting¬†them into the sea. See then what was the end of the wrongdoers"
  28,41,We made them leaders inviting ňĻothersňļ to the Fire. And on the Day of Judgment they will not be helped
  28,42,We caused a curse to follow them in this world. And on the Day of Judgment they will be among the outcasts
  28,43,"Indeed, We gave Moses the Scripture‚ÄĒafter destroying earlier nations‚ÄĒas an insight for the people, a guide, and mercy so perhaps they would be mindful"
  28,44,"You were not there ňĻO Prophetňļ on the western side of the mountain when We entrusted the Commandments to Moses, nor were you present ňĻin his timeňļ"
  28,45,"But We ňĻlaterňļ raised ňĻseveralňļ generations, and the ages took their toll on them.¬†Nor were you living among the people of Midian, rehearsing Our revelations with them. But it is We Who have sent ňĻthis¬†revelation to youňļ"
  28,46,"And you were not at the side of Mount ŠĻ¨√Ľr when We called out ňĻto Mosesňļ. But ňĻyou have been sentňļ as a mercy from your Lord to warn a people to whom no warner has come before you, so perhaps they may be mindful"
  28,47,"Also so they would not say, if struck by an affliction for what their hands have done: ‚ÄúOur Lord! If only You had sent us a messenger, we would have followed Your revelations and become believers.‚ÄĚ"
  28,48,"But when the truth came to them from Us, they said, ‚ÄúIf only he was given the like of what Moses had been given.‚ÄĚ¬†Did they not deny what had been given to Moses earlier? They claimed, ‚ÄúBoth ňĻScripturesňļ are works of magic, supporting each other!‚ÄĚ¬†Adding, ‚ÄúWe truly deny both.‚ÄĚ"
  28,49,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúBring then a scripture from God which is a better guide than these two so I may follow it, if your claim is true.‚ÄĚ"
  28,50,"So if they fail to respond to you, then know that they only follow their desires. And who could be more astray than those who follow their desires with no guidance from God? Surely God does not guide the wrongdoing people"
  28,51,"Indeed, We have steadily delivered the Word ňĻof Godňļ to the people so they may be mindful"
  28,52,"ňĻAs forňļ those ňĻfaithfulňļ to whom We had given the Scripture before this ňĻQuranňļ, they do believe in it"
  28,53,"When it is recited to them, they declare, ‚ÄúWe believe in it. This is definitely the truth from our Lord. We had already submitted¬†ňĻevenňļ before this.‚ÄĚ"
  28,54,"These ňĻbelieversňļ will be given a double reward for their perseverance, responding to evil with good, and for donating from what We have provided for them"
  28,55,"When they hear slanderous talk, they turn away from it, saying, ‚ÄúWe are accountable for our deeds and you for yours. Peace ňĻis our only responseňļ to you! We want nothing to do with those who act ignorantly.‚ÄĚ"
  28,56,"You surely cannot guide whoever you like ňĻO Prophetňļ, but it is God Who guides whoever He wills, and He knows best who are ňĻfit to beňļ guided"
  28,57,"They say ňĻto the Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúIf we were to follow ňĻtrueňļ guidance with you, we would certainly be snatched away from our land.‚ÄĚ Have We not established for them a safe haven ňĻin Meccaňļ to which fruits of all kinds are brought as a provision from Us? But most of them do not know ňĻthis favourňļ"
  28,58,"ňĻImagineňļ how many societies We have destroyed that had been spoiled by their ňĻcomfortableňļ living! Those are their residences, never inhabited after them except passingly.¬†And We ňĻaloneňļ were the Successor"
  28,59,"Your Lord would never destroy a society until He had sent to its capital a messenger, reciting Our revelations to them. Nor would We ever destroy a society unless its people persisted in wrongdoing"
  28,60,Whatever ňĻpleasureňļ you have been given is no more than ňĻa fleetingňļ enjoyment and adornment of this worldly life. But what is with God is far better and more lasting. Will you not then understand
  28,61,"Can those to whom We have made a fine promise‚ÄĒwhich they will see fulfilled‚ÄĒbe like those who We have allowed to enjoy the pleasures of this worldly life, but on the Day of Judgment will be brought ňĻfor punishmentňļ"
  28,62,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day He will call to them, ‚ÄúWhere are those you claimed were My associate-gods?‚ÄĚ"
  28,63,"Those ňĻmisleadersňļ against whom the decree ňĻof tormentňļ is justified will cry, ‚ÄúOur Lord! These ňĻfollowersňļ are the ones we caused to deviate. We led them into deviance, for we ourselves were deviant. We disassociate ourselves ňĻfrom themňļ before You. It was not us that they used to worship.‚ÄĚ"
  28,64,"It will be said ňĻto the disbelieversňļ, ‚ÄúCall upon your associate-gods ňĻfor helpňļ.‚ÄĚ So they will call them, but will receive no response. And they will face the punishment, wishing they had been ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  28,65,"And ňĻwatch forňļ the Day He will call to them, asking, ‚ÄúWhat response did you give to the messengers?‚ÄĚ"
  28,66,They will be too dumbstruck on that Day to ask one another ňĻfor answersňļ
  28,67,"As for those who repent, believe, and do good ňĻin this worldňļ, it is right to hope that they will be among the successful"
  28,68,Your Lord creates and chooses whatever He wills‚ÄĒthe choice is not theirs. Glorified and Exalted is God above what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ
  28,69,And your Lord knows what their hearts conceal and what they reveal
  28,70,He is God. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. All praise belongs to Him in this life and the next. All authority is His. And to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned
  28,71,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if God were to make the night perpetual for you until the Day of Judgment, which god other than God could bring you sunlight? Will you not then listen?‚ÄĚ"
  28,72,"Ask ňĻthem alsoňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if God were to make the day perpetual for you until the Day of Judgment, which god other than God could bring you night to rest in? Will you not then see?‚ÄĚ"
  28,73,"It is out of His mercy that He has made for you the day and night so that you may rest ňĻin the latterňļ and seek His bounty ňĻin the formerňļ, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  28,74,"And ňĻwatch forňļ the Day He will call to them, ‚ÄúWhere are those you claimed were My associate-gods?‚ÄĚ"
  28,75,"And We will bring forth a witness¬†from every faith-community and ask ňĻthe polytheistsňļ, ‚ÄúShow ňĻUsňļ your proof.‚ÄĚ Then they will ňĻcome toňļ know that the truth is with God ňĻaloneňļ. And whatever ňĻgodsňļ they fabricated will fail them"
  28,76,"Indeed, Korah¬†was from the people of Moses, but he behaved arrogantly towards them. We had granted him such treasures that even their keys would burden a group of strong men. ňĻSome ofňļ his people advised him, ‚ÄúDo not be prideful! Surely God does not like the prideful"
  28,77,"Rather, seek the ňĻrewardňļ of the Hereafter by means of what God has granted you, without forgetting your share of this world. And be good ňĻto othersňļ as God has been good to you. Do not seek to spread corruption in the land, for God certainly does not like the corruptors.‚ÄĚ"
  28,78,"He replied, ‚ÄúI have been granted all this because of some knowledge I have.‚ÄĚ¬†Did he not know that God had already destroyed some from the generations before him who were far superior to him in power and greater in accumulating ňĻwealthňļ? There will be no need for the wicked to be asked about their sins"
  28,79,"Then he came out before his people in all his glamour. Those who desired the life of this world wished, ‚ÄúIf only we could have something like what Korah has been given. He is truly a man of great fortune!‚ÄĚ"
  28,80,"But those gifted with knowledge said, ‚ÄúShame on you! God‚Äôs reward is far better for those who believe and do good. But none will attain this except the steadfast.‚ÄĚ"
  28,81,"Then We caused the earth to swallow him up, along with his home. There was no one to help him against God, nor could he even help himself"
  28,82,"And those who had craved his position the previous day began to say, ‚ÄúAh! It is certainly God Who gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. Had it not been for the grace of God, He could have surely caused the earth to swallow us up! Oh, indeed! The disbelievers will never succeed.‚ÄĚ"
  28,83,That ňĻeternalňļ Home in the Hereafter We reserve ňĻonlyňļ for those who seek neither tyranny nor corruption on the earth. The ultimate outcome belongs ňĻonlyňļ to the righteous
  28,84,"Whoever comes with a good deed will be rewarded with what is better. And whoever comes with an evil deed, then the evildoers will only be rewarded for what they used to do"
  28,85,"Most certainly, the One Who has ordained the Quran for you will ňĻultimatelyňļ bring you back home ňĻto Meccaňļ.¬†Say, ‚ÄúMy Lord knows best who has come with ňĻtrueňļ guidance and who is clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
  28,86,"You never expected this Book to be revealed to you, but ňĻit cameňļ only ňĻasňļ a mercy from your Lord. So never side with the disbelievers ňĻin their disbeliefňļ"
  28,87,"Do not let them turn you away from the revelations of God after they have been sent down to you. Rather, invite ňĻallňļ to ňĻthe Way ofňļ your Lord, and never be one of the polytheists"
  28,88,And do not invoke any other god with God. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. Everything is bound to perish except He Himself.¬†All authority belongs to Him. And to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned
  29,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m
  29,2,"Do people think once they say, ‚ÄúWe believe,‚ÄĚ that they will be left without being put to the test"
  29,3,We certainly tested those before them. And ňĻin this wayňļ God will clearly distinguish between those who are truthful and those who are liars
  29,4,Or do the evildoers ňĻsimplyňļ think that they will escape Us? How wrong is their judgment
  29,5,"Whoever hopes for the meeting with God, ňĻlet them know thatňļ God‚Äôs appointed time is sure to come. He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  29,6,"And whoever strives ňĻin God‚Äôs causeňļ, only does so for their own good. Surely God is not in need of ňĻany ofňļ His creation"
  29,7,"As for those who believe and do good, We will certainly absolve them of their sins, and reward them according to the best of what they used to do"
  29,8,"We have commanded people to honour their parents. But if they urge you to associate with Me what you have no knowledge of,¬†then do not obey them. To Me you will ňĻallňļ return, and then I will inform you of what you used to do"
  29,9,Those who believe and do good will surely be admitted by Us into ňĻthe company ofňļ the righteous
  29,10,"There are some who say, ‚ÄúWe believe in God,‚ÄĚ but when they suffer in the cause of God, they mistake ňĻthisňļ persecution at the hands of people for the punishment of God. But when victory comes from your Lord, they surely say ňĻto the believersňļ, ‚ÄúWe have always been with you.‚ÄĚ Does God not know best what is in the hearts of all beings"
  29,11,God will certainly distinguish between those who have ňĻsureňļ faith and the hypocrites
  29,12,"The disbelievers say to the believers, ‚ÄúňĻJustňļ follow our way, and we will bear ňĻthe burden ofňļ your sins.‚ÄĚ But they would never ňĻwant toňļ bear any of the believers‚Äô sins. They are simply lying"
  29,13,"Yet they will certainly ňĻbe made toňļ carry their own burdens, as well as other burdens along with their own.¬†And they will surely be questioned on Judgment Day about what they used to fabricate"
  29,14,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people, and he remained among them for a thousand years, less fifty. Then the Flood overtook them, while they persisted in wrongdoing"
  29,15,"But We delivered him and those in the Ark, making it a sign for all people"
  29,16,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham said to his people, ‚ÄúWorship God, and fear Him. This is better for you, if only you knew"
  29,17,"You worship besides God nothing but idols, simply creating lies ňĻabout themňļ. Those you worship besides God certainly cannot give you any provision. So seek provision from God ňĻaloneňļ, worship Him, and be grateful to Him. To Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  29,18,"If you ňĻMeccansňļ persist in denial, so did ňĻmanyňļ communities before you. The Messenger‚Äôs duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ clearly.‚ÄĚ"
  29,19,Have they not seen how God originates the creation then resurrects it? That is certainly easy for God
  29,20,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúTravel throughout the land and see how He originated the creation, then God will bring it into being one more time. Surely God is Most Capable of everything"
  29,21,"He punishes whoever He wills, and shows mercy to whoever He wills. And you will ňĻallňļ be returned to Him"
  29,22,And you cannot escape Him on earth or in heaven. Nor have you any protector or helper besides God.‚ÄĚ
  29,23,"As for those who disbelieve in God‚Äôs signs and the meeting with Him, it is they who will have no hope in His mercy.¬†And it is they who will suffer a painful punishment"
  29,24,"But the only response of Abraham‚Äôs people was to say: ‚ÄúKill him or burn him!‚ÄĚ But God saved him from the fire.¬†Surely in this are signs for people who believe"
  29,25,"He said ňĻto his peopleňļ, ‚ÄúYou have taken idols ňĻfor worshipňļ instead of God, only to keep ňĻthe bond ofňļ harmony among yourselves in this worldly life. But on the Day of Judgment you will disown and curse one another. Your home will be the Fire, and you will have no helper!‚ÄĚ"
  29,26,"So Lot believed in him. And Abraham said, ‚ÄúI am emigrating ňĻin obedienceňļ to my Lord. He ňĻaloneňļ is indeed the Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  29,27,"We blessed him with Isaac and ňĻlaterňļ Jacob, and reserved prophethood and revelation for his descendants. We gave him his reward in this life,¬†and in the Hereafter he will certainly be among the righteous"
  29,28,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Lot rebuked ňĻthe men ofňļ his people: ‚ÄúYou certainly commit a shameful deed that no man has ever done before you"
  29,29,"Do you really lust after ňĻotherňļ men, abuse the travellers, and practice immorality ňĻopenlyňļ in your gatherings?‚ÄĚ His people‚Äôs only response was to say ňĻmockinglyňļ: ‚ÄúBring God‚Äôs punishment upon us, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  29,30,"Lot prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Help me against the people of corruption.‚ÄĚ"
  29,31,"When Our messenger-angels came to Abraham with the good news ňĻof the birth of Isaacňļ, they said, ‚ÄúWe are going to destroy the people of this city ňĻof Sodomňļ, for its people have persisted in wrongdoing.‚ÄĚ"
  29,32,"He said, ‚ÄúBut Lot is there!‚ÄĚ They responded, ‚ÄúWe know best who is there. We will certainly save him and his family‚ÄĒexcept his wife, who is one of the doomed.‚ÄĚ"
  29,33,"And when Our messenger-angels came to Lot, he was distressed and worried by their arrival.¬†They reassured ňĻhimňļ, ‚ÄúDo not fear, nor grieve. We will surely deliver you and your family‚ÄĒexcept your wife, who is one of the doomed"
  29,34,We are certainly bringing down a punishment from heaven upon the people of this city for their rebelliousness.‚ÄĚ
  29,35,And We did leave ňĻsome ofňļ its ruins as a clear lesson for people of understanding
  29,36,"And to the people of Midian ňĻWe sentňļ their brother Shu‚Äôaib. He said, ‚ÄúO my people! Worship God, and hope for ňĻthe reward ofňļ the Last Day. And do not go about spreading corruption in the land.‚ÄĚ"
  29,37,"But they rejected him, so an ňĻoverwhelmingňļ earthquake struck them and they fell lifeless in their homes"
  29,38,"And the people of ‚Äô»ād and Tham√Ľd ňĻmet a similar fateňļ, which must be clear to you ňĻMeccansňļ from their ruins.¬†Satan made their ňĻevilňļ deeds appealing to them, hindering them from the ňĻRightňļ Way, although they were capable of reasoning"
  29,39,"ňĻWeňļ also ňĻdestroyedňļ Korah, Pharaoh, and Ham√Ęn. Indeed, Moses had come to them with clear proofs, but they behaved arrogantly in the land. Yet they could not escape ňĻUsňļ"
  29,40,"So We seized each ňĻpeopleňļ for their sin: against some of them We sent a storm of stones, some were overtaken by a ňĻmightyňļ blast, some We caused the earth to swallow, and some We drowned. God would not have wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  29,41,"The parable of those who take protectors other than God is that of a spider spinning a shelter. And the flimsiest of all shelters is certainly that of a spider, if only they knew"
  29,42,"God surely knows that whatever ňĻgodsňļ they invoke besides Him are ňĻsimplyňļ nothing. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  29,43,"These are the parables We set forth for humanity, but none will understand them except the people of knowledge"
  29,44,God created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. Surely in this is a sign for the people of faith
  29,45,"Recite what has been revealed to you of the Book and establish prayer. Indeed, ňĻgenuineňļ prayer should deter ňĻoneňļ from indecency and wickedness. The remembrance of God is ňĻanňļ even greater ňĻdeterrentňļ. And God ňĻfullyňļ knows what you ňĻallňļ do"
  29,46,"Do not argue with the People of the Book unless gracefully, except with those of them who act wrongfully. And say, ‚ÄúWe believe in what has been revealed to us and what was revealed to you. Our God and your God is ňĻonlyňļ One. And to Him we ňĻfullyňļ submit.‚ÄĚ"
  29,47,"Similarly ňĻto earlier messengersňļ, We have revealed to you a Book ňĻO Prophetňļ. ňĻThe faithful ofňļ those to whom We gave the Scriptures believe in it, as do some of these ňĻpagan Arabsňļ. And none denies Our revelations except the ňĻstubbornňļ disbelievers"
  29,48,"You ňĻO Prophetňļ could not read any writing ňĻevenňļ before this ňĻrevelationňļ, nor could you write at all. Otherwise, the people of falsehood would have been suspicious"
  29,49,But this ňĻQuranňļ is ňĻa set ofňļ clear revelations ňĻpreservedňļ in the hearts of those gifted with knowledge. And none denies Our revelations except the ňĻstubbornňļ wrongdoers
  29,50,"They say, ‚ÄúIf only ňĻsomeňļ signs had been sent down to him from his Lord!‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSigns are only with God. And I am only sent with a clear warning.‚ÄĚ"
  29,51,"Is it not enough for them that We have sent down to you the Book, ňĻwhich isňļ recited to them. Surely in this ňĻQuranňļ is a mercy and reminder for people who believe"
  29,52,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSufficient is God as a Witness between me and you. He ňĻfullyňļ knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth. And those who believe in falsehood and disbelieve in God, it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ losers.‚ÄĚ"
  29,53,"They challenge you ňĻO Prophetňļ to hasten the punishment. Had it not been for a time already set, the punishment would have certainly come to them ňĻat onceňļ. But it will definitely take them by surprise when they least expect it"
  29,54,They urge you to hasten the punishment. And Hell will certainly encompass the disbelievers
  29,55,"on the Day the punishment will overwhelm them from above them and from below their feet. And it will be said, ‚ÄúReap what you sowed.‚ÄĚ"
  29,56,"O My believing servants! My earth is truly spacious, so worship Me ňĻaloneňļ"
  29,57,"Every soul will taste death, then to Us you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  29,58,"ňĻAs forňļ those who believe and do good, We will certainly house them in ňĻelevatedňļ mansions in Paradise, under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. How excellent is the reward for those who work ňĻrighteousness!ňļ‚ÄĒ"
  29,59,"those who patiently endure, and put their trust in their Lord"
  29,60,"How many are the creatures that cannot secure their provisions! ňĻIt isňļ God ňĻWhoňļ provides for them and you ňĻas wellňļ. He is indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  29,61,"If you ask them ňĻO Prophetňļ who created the heavens and the earth and subjected the sun and the moon ňĻfor your benefitňļ, they will certainly say, ‚ÄúGod!‚ÄĚ How can they then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  29,62,God gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. Surely God has ňĻfullňļ knowledge of everything
  29,63,"And if you ask them who sends down rain from the sky, giving life to the earth after its death, they will surely say, ‚ÄúGod!‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúPraise be to God!‚ÄĚ In fact, most of them do not understand"
  29,64,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement. But the Hereafter is indeed the real life, if only they knew"
  29,65,"If they happen to be aboard a ship ňĻcaught in a stormňļ, they cry out to God ňĻaloneňļ in sincere devotion. But as soon as He delivers them ňĻsafelyňļ to shore, they associate ňĻothers with Him once againňļ"
  29,66,"So let them be ungrateful for all We have given them, and ňĻlet themňļ enjoy themselves ňĻfor nowňļ! For they will soon know"
  29,67,"Have they not seen how We have made ňĻMeccaňļ a safe haven, whereas people ňĻallňļ around them are snatched away?¬†How can they then believe in falsehood¬†and deny God‚Äôs favours"
  29,68,And who does more wrong than those who fabricate lies against God or reject the truth after it has reached them? Is Hell not a ňĻfittingňļ home for the disbelievers
  29,69,"As for those who struggle in Our cause, We will surely guide them along Our Way. And God is certainly with the good-doers"
