  30,5,"at the victory willed by God. He gives victory to whoever He wills. For He is the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  30,6,ňĻThis isňļ the promise of God. ňĻAndňļ God never fails in His promise. But most people do not know
  30,7,"They ňĻonlyňļ know the worldly affairs of this life, but are ňĻtotallyňļ oblivious to the Hereafter"
  30,8,Have they not reflected upon their own being? God only created the heavens and the earth and everything in between for a purpose and an appointed term. Yet most people are truly in denial of the meeting with their Lord
  30,9,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them? They were far superior in might; they cultivated the land and developed it more than these ňĻMeccansňļ ever have. Their messengers came to them with clear proofs. God would have never wronged them, but it was they who wronged themselves"
  30,10,Then most evil was the end of the evildoers for denying and mocking the signs of God
  30,11,"It is God Who originates the creation, and will resurrect it. And then to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  30,12,"On the Day the Hour will arrive, the wicked will be dumbstruck"
  30,13,"There will be no intercessors for them from among their associate-gods, and they will ňĻtotallyňļ deny their associate-gods"
  30,14,"And on the Day the Hour will arrive, the people will then be split ňĻinto two groupsňļ"
  30,15,"As for those who believed and did good, they will be rejoicing in a Garden"
  30,16,"And as for those who disbelieved, and denied Our signs and the meeting ňĻwith Godňļ in the Hereafter, they will be confined in punishment"
  30,17,So glorify God in the evening and in the morning‚ÄĒ
  30,18,"all praise is for Him in the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒas well as in the afternoon, and at noon"
  30,19,He brings forth the living from the dead and the dead from the living. And He gives life to the earth after its death. And so will you be brought forth ňĻfrom the graveňļ
  30,20,"One of His signs is that He created you from dust, then‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒyou are human beings spreading over ňĻthe earthňļ"
  30,21,And one of His signs is that He created for you spouses from among yourselves so that you may find comfort in them. And He has placed between you compassion and mercy. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect
  30,22,"And one of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the diversity of your languages and colours. Surely in this are signs for those of ňĻsoundňļ knowledge"
  30,23,And one of His signs is your sleep by night and by day ňĻfor restňļ as well as your seeking His bounty ňĻin bothňļ. Surely in this are signs for people who listen
  30,24,"And one of His signs is that He shows you lightning, inspiring ňĻyou withňļ hope and fear.¬†And He sends down rain from the sky, reviving the earth after its death. Surely in this are signs for people who understand"
  30,25,"And one of His signs is that the heavens and the earth persist by His command. Then when He calls you out of the earth just once, you will instantly come forth"
  30,26,And to Him belong all those in the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒall are subject to His Will
  30,27,"And He is the One Who originates the creation then will resurrect it‚ÄĒwhich is even easier for Him.¬†To Him belong the finest attributes in the heavens and the earth. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  30,28,"He sets forth for you an example ňĻdrawnňļ from your own lives: would you allow some of those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in your possession to be your equal partners in whatever ňĻwealthňļ We have provided you, keeping them in mind as you are mindful of your peers?¬†This is how We make the signs clear for people who understand"
  30,29,"In fact, the wrongdoers merely follow their desires with no knowledge. Who then can guide those God has left to stray? They will have no helpers"
  30,30,"So be steadfast in faith in all uprightness ňĻO Prophetňļ‚ÄĒthe natural Way of God which He has instilled in ňĻallňļ people. Let there be no change in this creation of God. That is the Straight Way, but most people do not know"
  30,31,"ňĻO believers!ňļ Always turn to Him ňĻin repentanceňļ, be mindful of Him, and establish prayers. And do not be polytheists‚ÄĒ"
  30,32,"ňĻlikeňļ those who have divided their faith and split into sects, each rejoicing in what they have"
  30,33,"When people are touched with hardship, they cry out to their Lord, turning to Him ňĻaloneňļ. But as soon as He gives them a taste of His mercy, a group of them associates ňĻothersňļ with their Lord ňĻin worshipňļ"
  30,34,"becoming ungrateful for whatever ňĻfavoursňļ We have given them. So enjoy yourselves, for soon you will know"
  30,35,Or have We sent down to them an authority which attests to what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ
  30,36,"If We give people a taste of mercy, they become prideful ňĻbecauseňļ of it. But if they are afflicted with an evil for what their hands have done, they instantly fall into despair"
  30,37,Have they not seen that God gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills? Surely in this are signs for people who believe
  30,38,"So give your close relatives their due, as well as the poor and the ňĻneedyňļ traveller. That is best for those who seek the pleasure of God,¬†and it is they who will be successful"
  30,39,"Whatever loans you give, ňĻonlyňļ seeking interest at the expense of people‚Äôs wealth¬†will not increase with God. But whatever charity you give, ňĻonlyňļ seeking the pleasure of God‚ÄĒit is they whose reward will be multiplied"
  30,40,"It is God Who created you, then gives you provisions, then will cause you to die, and then will bring you back to life. Can any of your associate-gods do any of this? Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate with Him ňĻin worshipňļ"
  30,41,"Corruption has spread on land and sea as a result of what people‚Äôs hands have done, so that God may cause them to taste ňĻthe consequences ofňļ some of their deeds and perhaps they might return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  30,42,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúTravel throughout the land and see what was the end of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before ňĻyouňļ‚ÄĒmost of them were polytheists.‚ÄĚ"
  30,43,"So be steadfast in the Upright Faith ňĻO Prophetňļ, before the coming of a Day from God that cannot be averted. On that Day the people will be divided"
  30,44,those who disbelieved will bear ňĻthe burden ofňļ their own disbelief; and those who did good will have prepared for themselves ňĻeternal homesňļ
  30,45,"so that He may ňĻgenerouslyňļ reward those who believe and do good, out of His grace. He truly does not like the disbelievers"
  30,46,"And one of His signs is that He sends the winds, ushering in good news ňĻof rainňļ so that He may give you a taste of His mercy, and that ships may sail by His command, and that you may seek His bounty, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  30,47,"Indeed, We sent before you ňĻO Prophetňļ messengers, each to their own people, and they came to them with clear proofs. Then We inflicted punishment upon those who persisted in wickedness. For it is Our duty to help the believers"
  30,48,"It is God Who sends the winds, which then stir up ňĻvapour, formingňļ clouds, which He then spreads out in the sky or piles up into masses as He wills, from which you see rain come forth. Then as soon as He causes it to fall on whoever He wills of His servants, they rejoice"
  30,49,although they had utterly lost hope just before it was sent down to them
  30,50,"See then the impact of God‚Äôs mercy: how He gives life to the earth after its death! Surely That ňĻsame Godňļ can raise the dead. For He is Most Capable of everything"
  30,51,"Then if We send a ňĻharshňļ wind which they see withering ňĻtheirňļ crops, they will definitely deny ňĻold favoursňļ right after"
  30,52,So you ňĻO Prophetňļ certainly cannot make the dead hear ňĻthe truthňļ. Nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and walk away
  30,53,"Nor can you lead the blind out of their misguidance. You can make none hear ňĻthe truthňļ except those who believe in Our revelations, ňĻfullyňļ submitting ňĻto Godňļ"
  30,54,"It is God Who created you in a state of weakness, then developed ňĻyourňļ weakness into strength, then developed ňĻyourňļ strength into weakness and old age.¬†He creates whatever He wills. For He is the All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  30,55,"And on the Day the Hour will arrive, the wicked will swear that they did not stay ňĻin this worldňļ more than an hour. In this way they were always deluded ňĻin the worldňļ"
  30,56,"But those gifted with knowledge and faith will say ňĻto themňļ, ‚ÄúYou did actually stay‚ÄĒas destined by God‚ÄĒuntil the Day of Resurrection. So here is the Day of Resurrection ňĻwhich you deniedňļ! But you did not know ňĻit was trueňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  30,57,"So on that Day the wrongdoers‚Äô excuses will not benefit them, nor will they be allowed to appease ňĻtheir Lordňļ"
  30,58,"We have certainly set forth every ňĻkind ofňļ lesson for people in this Quran. And no matter what sign you bring to them ňĻO Prophetňļ, the disbelievers will definitely say ňĻto the believersňļ, ‚ÄúYou are only a people of falsehood.‚ÄĚ"
  30,59,This is how God seals the hearts of those unwilling to know ňĻthe truthňļ
  30,60,"So be patient, for the promise of God certainly is true. And do not be disturbed by those who have no sure faith"
