  31,7,"Whenever Our revelations are recited to them, they turn away in arrogance as if they did not hear them, as if there is deafness in their ears. So give them good news ňĻO Prophetňļ of a painful punishment"
  31,8,Surely those who believe and do good will have the Gardens of Bliss
  31,9,"staying there forever. God‚Äôs promise is true. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  31,10,"He created the heavens without pillars‚ÄĒas you can see‚ÄĒand placed firm mountains upon the earth so it does not shake with you, and scattered throughout it all types of creatures. And We send down rain from the sky, causing every type of fine plant to grow on earth"
  31,11,"This is God‚Äôs creation. Now show Me what those ňĻgodsňļ other than Him have created. In fact, the wrongdoers are clearly astray"
  31,12,"Indeed, We blessed Luqm√Ęn with wisdom, ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúBe grateful to God, for whoever is grateful, it is only for their own good. And whoever is ungrateful, then surely God is Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy.‚ÄĚ"
  31,13,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Luqm√Ęn said to his son, while advising him, ‚ÄúO my dear son! Never associate ňĻanythingňļ with God ňĻin worshipňļ, for associating ňĻothers with Himňļ is truly the worst of all wrongs.‚ÄĚ"
  31,14,"And We have commanded people to ňĻhonourňļ their parents. Their mothers bore them through hardship upon hardship, and their weaning takes two years. So be grateful to Me and your parents.¬†To Me is the final return"
  31,15,"But if they pressure you to associate with Me what you have no knowledge of,¬†do not obey them. Still keep their company in this world courteously, and follow the way of those who turn to Me ňĻin devotionňļ. Then to Me you will ňĻallňļ return, and then I will inform you of what you used to do"
  31,16,"ňĻLuqm√Ęn added,ňļ ‚ÄúO my dear son! ňĻEvenňļ if a deed were the weight of a mustard seed‚ÄĒbe it ňĻhiddenňļ in a rock or in the heavens or the earth‚ÄĒGod will bring it forth. Surely God is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  31,17,"‚ÄúO my dear son! Establish prayer, encourage what is good and forbid what is evil, and endure patiently whatever befalls you. Surely this is a resolve to aspire to"
  31,18,"‚ÄúAnd do not turn your nose up to people, nor walk pridefully upon the earth. Surely God does not like whoever is arrogant, boastful"
  31,19,"Be moderate in your pace. And lower your voice, for the ugliest of all voices is certainly the braying of donkeys.‚ÄĚ"
  31,20,"Have you not seen that God has subjected for you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth, and has lavished His favours upon you, both seen and unseen? ňĻStillňļ there are some who dispute about God without knowledge, or guidance, or an enlightening scripture"
  31,21,"When it is said to them, ‚ÄúFollow what God has revealed,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúNo! We ňĻonlyňļ follow what we found our forefathers practicing.‚ÄĚ ňĻWould they still do soňļ even if Satan is inviting them to the torment of the Blaze"
  31,22,"Whoever fully submits themselves to God and is a good-doer, they have certainly grasped the firmest hand-hold. And with God rests the outcome of ňĻallňļ affairs"
  31,23,"But whoever disbelieves, do not let their disbelief grieve you ňĻO Prophetňļ. To Us is their return, and We will inform them of all they did. Surely God knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  31,24,"We allow them enjoyment for a little while, then ňĻin timeňļ We will force them into a harsh torment"
  31,25,"And if you ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will definitely say, ‚ÄúGod!‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúPraise be to God!‚ÄĚ In fact, most of them do not know"
  31,26,"To God belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. God is truly the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  31,27,"If all the trees on earth were pens and the ocean ňĻwere inkňļ, refilled by seven other oceans, the Words of God would not be exhausted. Surely God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  31,28,"The creation and resurrection of you ňĻallňļ is as simple ňĻfor Himňļ as that of a single soul. Surely God is All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  31,29,"Do you not see that God causes the night to merge into the day and the day into the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term, and that God is All-Aware of what you do"
  31,30,"That is because God ňĻaloneňļ is the Truth and what they invoke besides Him is falsehood, and ňĻbecauseňļ God ňĻaloneňļ is the Most High, All-Great"
  31,31,"Do you not see that the ships sail ňĻsmoothlyňļ through the sea by the grace of God so that He may show you some of His signs? Surely in this are signs for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  31,32,"And as soon as they are overwhelmed by waves like mountains, they cry out to God ňĻaloneňļ in sincere devotion. But when He delivers them ňĻsafelyňļ to shore, only some become relatively grateful. And none rejects Our signs except whoever is deceitful, ungrateful"
  31,33,"O humanity! Be mindful of your Lord, and beware of a Day when no parent will be of any benefit to their child, nor will a child be of any benefit to their parent. Surely God‚Äôs promise is true. So do not let the life of this world deceive you, nor let the Chief Deceiver¬†deceive you about God"
  31,34,"Indeed, God ňĻaloneňļ has the knowledge of the Hour. He sends down the rain,¬†and knows what is in the wombs.¬†No soul knows what it will earn for tomorrow, and no soul knows in what land it will die. Surely God is All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  32,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m
  32,2,The revelation of this Book is‚ÄĒbeyond doubt‚ÄĒfrom the Lord of all worlds
  32,3,"Or do they say, ‚ÄúHe has fabricated it!‚ÄĚ? No! It is the truth from your Lord in order for you to warn a people to whom no warner has come before you, so they may be ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  32,4,"It is God Who has created the heavens and the earth and everything in between in six Days,¬†then established Himself on the Throne. You have no protector or intercessor besides Him. Will you not then be mindful"
  32,5,"He conducts every affair from the heavens to the earth, then it all ascends to Him on a Day whose length is a thousand years by your counting"
  32,6,"That is the Knower of the seen and unseen‚ÄĒthe Almighty, Most Merciful"
  32,7,Who has perfected everything He created. And He originated the creation of humankind from clay
  32,8,Then He made his descendants from an extract of a humble fluid
  32,9,"then He fashioned them and had a spirit of His Own ňĻcreationňļ breathed into them. And He gave you hearing, sight, and intellect. ňĻYetňļ you hardly give any thanks"
  32,10,"ňĻStillňļ they ask ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhen we are disintegrated into the earth, will we really be raised as a new creation?‚ÄĚ In fact, they are in denial of the meeting with their Lord"
  32,11,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYour soul will be taken by the Angel of Death, who is in charge of you. Then to your Lord you will ňĻallňļ be returned.‚ÄĚ"
  32,12,"If only you could see the wicked hanging their heads ňĻin shameňļ before their Lord, ňĻcrying:ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! We have now seen and heard, so send us back and we will do good. We truly have sure faith ňĻnowňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  32,13,"Had We willed, We could have easily imposed guidance on every soul. But My Word will come to pass: I will surely fill up Hell with jinn and humans all together"
  32,14,So taste ňĻthe punishmentňļ for neglecting the meeting of this Day of yours. We ňĻtooňļ will certainly neglect you. And taste the torment of eternity for what you used to do
  32,15,The only ňĻtrueňļ believers in Our revelation are those who‚ÄĒwhen it is recited to them‚ÄĒfall into prostration and glorify the praises of their Lord and are not too proud
  32,16,"They abandon their beds, invoking their Lord with hope and fear, and donate from what We have provided for them"
  32,17,No soul can imagine what delights are kept in store for them as a reward for what they used to do
  32,18,Is the one who is a believer equal ňĻbefore Godňļ to the one who is rebellious? They are not equal
  32,19,"As for those who believe and do good, they will have the Gardens of ňĻEternalňļ Residence‚ÄĒas an accommodation for what they used to do"
  32,20,"But as for those who are rebellious, the Fire will be their home. Whenever they try to escape from it, they will be forced back into it, and will be told, ‚ÄúTaste the Fire‚Äôs torment, which you used to deny.‚ÄĚ"
  32,21,"We will certainly make them taste some of the minor torment ňĻin this lifeňļ before the major torment ňĻof the Hereafterňļ, so perhaps they will return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  32,22,And who does more wrong than the one who is reminded of God‚Äôs revelations then turns away from them? We will surely inflict punishment upon the wicked
  32,23,"Indeed, We gave the Scripture to Moses‚ÄĒso let there be no doubt ňĻO Prophetňļ that you ňĻtooňļ are receiving revelations‚ÄĒand We made it a guide for the Children of Israel"
  32,24,"We raised from among them leaders,¬†guiding by Our command, when they patiently endured and firmly believed in Our signs"
  32,25,"Indeed, your Lord will decide between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their differences"
  32,26,"Is it not yet clear to them how many peoples We destroyed before them, whose ruins they still pass by? Surely in this are signs. Will they not then listen"
  32,27,"Do they not see how We drive rain to parched land, producing ňĻvariousňļ crops from which they and their cattle eat? Will they not then see"
  32,28,"They ask ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhen is this ňĻDay of finalňļ Decision, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  32,29,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúOn the Day of Decision it will not benefit the disbelievers to believe then, nor will they be delayed ňĻfrom punishmentňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  32,30,"So turn away from them, and wait! They too are waiting"
  33,1,"O Prophet! ňĻAlwaysňļ be mindful of God, and do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Indeed, God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  33,2,Follow what is revealed to you from your Lord. Surely God is All-Aware of what you ňĻallňļ do
  33,3,"And put your trust in God, for God is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,4,"God does not place two hearts in any person‚Äôs chest. Nor does He regard your wives as ňĻunlawful for you likeňļ your real mothers, ňĻevenňļ if you say they are.¬†Nor does He regard your adopted children as your real children.¬†These are only your baseless assertions. But God declares the truth, and He ňĻaloneňļ guides to the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  33,5,"Let your adopted children keep their family names. That is more just in the sight of God. But if you do not know their fathers, then they are ňĻsimplyňļ your fellow believers and close associates. There is no blame on you for what you do by mistake, but ňĻonlyňļ for what you do intentionally. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,6,"The Prophet has a stronger affinity to the believers than they do themselves. And his wives are their mothers. As ordained by God, blood relatives are more entitled ňĻto inheritanceňļ than ňĻotherňļ believers and immigrants, unless you ňĻwant toňļ show kindness to your ňĻcloseňļ associates ňĻthrough bequestňļ.¬†This is decreed in the Record"
  33,7,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took a covenant from the prophets, as well as from you ňĻO Prophetňļ, and from Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, son of Mary. We did take a solemn covenant from ňĻall ofňļ them"
  33,8,so that He may question these men of truth about their ňĻdelivery of theňļ truth. And He has prepared a painful punishment for the disbelievers
  33,9,"O believers! Remember God‚Äôs favour upon you when ňĻenemyňļ forces came to ňĻbesiegeňļ you ňĻin Medinaňļ,¬†so We sent against them a ňĻbitterňļ wind and forces you could not see.¬†And God is All-Seeing of what you do"
  33,10,"ňĻRememberňļ when they came at you from east and west,¬†when your eyes grew wild ňĻin horrorňļ and your hearts jumped into your throats, and you entertained ňĻconflictingňļ thoughts about God"
  33,11,"Then and there the believers were put to the test, and were violently shaken"
  33,12,"And ňĻrememberňļ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, ‚ÄúGod and His Messenger have promised us nothing but delusion!‚ÄĚ"
  33,13,"And ňĻrememberňļ when a group of them said, ‚ÄúO people of Yathrib!¬†There is no point in you staying ňĻhereňļ, so retreat!‚ÄĚ Another group of them asked the Prophet‚Äôs permission ňĻto leaveňļ, saying, ‚ÄúOur homes are vulnerable,‚ÄĚ while ňĻin factňļ they were not vulnerable. They only wished to flee"
  33,14,"Had their city been sacked from all sides and they had been asked to abandon faith, they would have done so with little hesitation"
  33,15,They had already pledged to God earlier never to turn their backs ňĻin retreatňļ. And a pledge to God must be answered for
  33,16,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúFleeing will not benefit you if you ňĻtry toňļ escape a natural or violent death. ňĻIf it is not your time,ňļ you will only be allowed enjoyment for a little while.‚ÄĚ"
  33,17,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho can put you out of God‚Äôs reach if He intends to harm you or show you mercy?‚ÄĚ They can never find any protector or helper besides God"
  33,18,"God knows well those among you who discourage ňĻothers from fightingňļ, saying ňĻsecretlyňļ to their brothers, ‚ÄúStay with us,‚ÄĚ and who themselves hardly take part in fighting"
  33,19,"ňĻThey areňļ totally unwilling to assist you. When danger comes, you see them staring at you with their eyes rolling like someone in the throes of death. But once the danger is over, they slash you with razor-sharp tongues, ravenous for ňĻworldlyňļ gains. Such people have not ňĻtrulyňļ believed, so God has rendered their deeds void. And that is easy for God"
  33,20,"They ňĻstillňļ think that the enemy alliance has not ňĻyetňļ withdrawn. And if the allies were to come ňĻagainňļ, the hypocrites would wish to be away in the desert among nomadic Arabs, ňĻonlyňļ asking for news about you ňĻbelieversňļ. And if the hypocrites were in your midst, they would hardly take part in the fight"
  33,21,"Indeed, in the Messenger of God you have an excellent example for whoever has hope in God and the Last Day, and remembers God often"
  33,22,"When the believers saw the enemy alliance, they said, ‚ÄúThis is what God and His Messenger had promised us. The promise of God and His Messenger has come true.‚ÄĚ And this only increased them in faith and submission"
  33,23,"Among the believers are men who have proven true to what they pledged to God.¬†Some of them have fulfilled their pledge ňĻwith their livesňļ, others are waiting ňĻtheir turnňļ. They have never changed ňĻtheir commitmentňļ in the least"
  33,24,"ňĻIt all happenedňļ so God may reward the faithful for their faithfulness, and punish the hypocrites if He wills or turn to them ňĻin mercyňļ. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,25,"And God drove back the disbelievers in their rage, totally empty-handed. And God spared the believers from fighting. For God is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  33,26,"And He brought down those from the People of the Book¬†who supported the enemy alliance from their own strongholds, and cast horror into their hearts. You ňĻbelieversňļ killed some, and took others captive"
  33,27,"He has also caused you to take over their lands, homes, and wealth, as well as lands you have not yet set foot on. And God is Most Capable of everything"
  33,28,"O Prophet! Say to your wives, ‚ÄúIf you desire the life of this world and its luxury, then come, I will give you a ňĻsuitableňļ compensation ňĻfor divorceňļ and let you go graciously"
  33,29,"But if you desire God and His Messenger and the ňĻeverlastingňļ Home of the Hereafter, then Surely God has prepared a great reward for those of you who do good.‚ÄĚ"
  33,30,"O wives of the Prophet! If any of you were to commit a blatant misconduct, the punishment would be doubled for her. And that is easy for God"
  33,31,"And whoever of you devoutly obeys God and His Messenger and does good, We will grant her double the reward, and We have prepared for her an honourable provision"
  33,32,"O wives of the Prophet! You are not like any other women: if you are mindful ňĻof Godňļ, then do not be overly effeminate in speech ňĻwith menňļ or those with sickness in their hearts may be tempted, but speak in a moderate tone"
  33,33,"Settle in your homes, and do not display yourselves as women did in the days of ňĻpre-Islamicňļ ignorance. Establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and obey God and His Messenger. God only intends to keep ňĻthe causes ofňļ evil away from you and purify you completely, O members of the ňĻProphet‚Äôsňļ family"
  33,34,"ňĻAlwaysňļ remember what is recited in your homes of God‚Äôs revelations and ňĻpropheticňļ wisdom.¬†Surely God is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  33,35,"Surely ňĻforňļ Muslim men and women, believing men and women,¬†devout men and women, truthful men and women, patient men and women, humble men and women, charitable men and women, fasting men and women, men and women who guard their chastity, and men and women who remember God often‚ÄĒfor ňĻall ofňļ them God has prepared forgiveness and a great reward"
  33,36,"It is not for a believing man or woman‚ÄĒwhen God and His Messenger decree a matter‚ÄĒto have any other choice in that matter.¬†Indeed, whoever disobeys God and His Messenger has clearly gone ňĻfarňļ astray"
  33,37,"And ňĻremember, O Prophet,ňļ when you said to the one¬†for whom God has done a favour and you ňĻtooňļ have done a favour,¬†‚ÄúKeep your wife and fear God,‚ÄĚ while concealing within yourself what God was going to reveal. And ňĻsoňļ you were considering the people, whereas God was more worthy of your consideration. So when Zaid totally lost interest in ňĻkeepingňļ his wife, We gave her to you in marriage, so that there would be no blame on the believers for marrying the ex-wives of their adopted sons after their divorce. And God‚Äôs command is totally binding"
  33,38,There is no blame on the Prophet for doing what God has ordained for him. That has been the way of God with those ňĻprophetsňļ who had gone before. And God‚Äôs command has been firmly decreed
  33,39,"ňĻThat is His way withňļ those ňĻprophetsňļ who deliver the messages of God, and consider Him, and none but God. And sufficient is God as a ňĻvigilantňļ Reckoner"
  33,40,"MuŠł•ammad is not the father of any of your men,¬†but is the Messenger of God and the seal of the prophets. And God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  33,41,O believers! Always remember God often
  33,42,and glorify Him morning and evening
  33,43,He is the One Who showers His blessings upon you‚ÄĒand His angels pray for you‚ÄĒso that He may bring you out of darkness and into light. For He is ever Merciful to the believers
  33,44,"Their greeting on the Day they meet Him will be, ‚ÄúPeace!‚ÄĚ And He has prepared for them an honourable reward"
  33,45,"O Prophet! We have sent you as a witness, and a deliverer of good news, and a warner"
  33,46,"and a caller to ňĻthe Way ofňļ God by His command, and a beacon of light"
  33,47,Give good news to the believers that they will have a great bounty from God
  33,48,"Do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Overlook their annoyances, and put your trust in God. For God is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,49,"O believers! If you marry believing women and then divorce them before you touch them,¬†they will have no waiting period for you to count,¬†so give them a ňĻsuitableňļ compensation, and let them go graciously"
  33,50,"O Prophet! We have made lawful for you your wives to whom you have paid their ňĻfullňļ dowries as well as those ňĻbondwomenňļ in your possession, whom God has granted you.¬†And ňĻyou are allowed to marryňļ the daughters of your paternal uncles and aunts, and the daughters of your maternal uncles and aunts, who have emigrated like you. Also ňĻallowed for marriage isňļ a believing woman who offers herself to the Prophet ňĻwithout dowryňļ if he is interested in marrying her‚ÄĒňĻthis isňļ exclusively for you, not for the rest of the believers.¬†We know well what ňĻrulingsňļ We have ordained for the believers in relation to their wives and those ňĻbondwomenňļ in their possession. As such, there would be no blame on you. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,51,"It is up to you ňĻO Prophetňļ to delay or receive whoever you please of your wives. There is no blame on you if you call back any of those you have set aside.¬†That is more likely that they will be content, not grieved, and satisfied with what you offer them all. God ňĻfullyňļ knows what is in your hearts. And God is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  33,52,"It is not lawful for you ňĻO Prophetňļ to marry more women after this, nor can you replace any of your present wives with another, even if her beauty may attract you‚ÄĒexcept those ňĻbondwomenňļ in your possession. And God is ever Watchful over all things"
  33,53,"O believers! Do not enter the homes of the Prophet without permission ňĻand if invitedňļ for a meal, do not ňĻcome too early andňļ linger until the meal is ready. But if you are invited, then enter ňĻon timeňļ. Once you have eaten, then go on your way, and do not stay for casual talk. Such behaviour is truly annoying to the Prophet, yet he is too shy to ask you to leave. But God is never shy of the truth. And when you ňĻbelieversňļ ask his wives for something, ask them from behind a barrier. This is purer for your hearts and theirs. And it is not right for you to annoy the Messenger of God, nor ever marry his wives after him. This would certainly be a major offence in the sight of God"
  33,54,"Whether you reveal something or conceal it, surely God has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  33,55,"There is no blame on the Prophet‚Äôs wives ňĻif they appear unveiledňļ before their fathers,¬†their sons, their brothers, their brothers‚Äô sons, their sisters‚Äô sons, their fellow ňĻMuslimňļ women, and those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in their possession. And be mindful of God ňĻO wives of the Prophet!ňļ Surely God is a Witness over all things"
  33,56,"Indeed, God showers His blessings upon the Prophet, and His angels pray for him. O believers! Invoke God‚Äôs blessings upon him, and salute him with worthy greetings of peace"
  33,57,Surely those who offend God¬†and His Messenger¬†are condemned by God in this world and the Hereafter. And He has prepared for them a humiliating punishment
  33,58,"As for those who abuse believing men and women¬†unjustifiably, they will definitely bear the guilt of slander and blatant sin"
  33,59,"O Prophet! Ask your wives, daughters, and believing women to draw their cloaks over their bodies. In this way it is more likely that they will be recognized ňĻas virtuousňļ and not be harassed. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,60,"If the hypocrites, and those with sickness in their hearts, and rumour-mongers in Medina do not desist, We will certainly incite you ňĻO Prophetňļ against them, and then they will not be your neighbours there any longer"
  33,61,"ňĻThey deserve to beňļ condemned. ňĻIf they were to persist,ňļ they would get themselves seized and killed relentlessly wherever they are found"
  33,62,That was God‚Äôs way with those ňĻhypocritesňļ who have gone before. And you will find no change in God‚Äôs way
  33,63,"People ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about the Hour. Say, ‚ÄúThat knowledge is only with God. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near.‚ÄĚ"
  33,64,"Surely God condemns the disbelievers, and has prepared for them a blazing Fire"
  33,65,to stay there for ever and ever‚ÄĒnever will they find any protector or helper
  33,66,"On the Day their faces are ňĻconstantlyňļ flipped in the Fire, they will cry, ‚ÄúOh! If only we had obeyed God and obeyed the Messenger!‚ÄĚ"
  33,67,"And they will say, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We obeyed our leaders and elite, but they led us astray from the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  33,68,"Our Lord! Give them double ňĻourňļ punishment, and condemn them tremendously.‚ÄĚ"
  33,69,"O believers! Do not be like those who slandered Moses, but God cleared him of what they said. And he was honourable in the sight of God"
  33,70,"O believers! Be mindful of God, and say what is right"
  33,71,"He will bless your deeds for you, and forgive your sins. And whoever obeys God and His Messenger, has truly achieved a great triumph"
  33,72,"Indeed, We offered the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they ňĻallňļ declined to bear it, being fearful of it. But humanity assumed it, ňĻforňļ they are truly wrongful ňĻto themselvesňļ and ignorant ňĻof the consequencesňļ"
  33,73,"so that God will punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, and God will turn in mercy to believing men and women. For God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  34,1,"All praise is for God, to Whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And praise be to Him in the Hereafter. He is the All-Wise, All-Aware"
  34,2,"He knows whatever goes into the earth and whatever comes out of it, and whatever descends from the sky and whatever ascends into it. And He is the Most Merciful, All-Forgiving"
  34,3,"The disbelievers say, ‚ÄúThe Hour will never come to us.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYes‚ÄĒby my Lord, the Knower of the unseen‚ÄĒit will certainly come to you!‚ÄĚ Not ňĻevenňļ an atom‚Äôs weight is hidden from Him in the heavens or the earth; nor anything smaller or larger than that, but is ňĻwrittenňļ in a perfect Record"
  34,4,So He may reward those who believe and do good. It is they who will have forgiveness and an honourable provision
  34,5,"As for those who strive to discredit Our revelations, it is they who will suffer the ňĻworstňļ torment of agonizing pain"
  34,6,"Those gifted with knowledge ňĻclearlyňļ see that what has been revealed to you from your Lord ňĻO Prophetňļ is the truth, and that it guides to the Path of the Almighty, the Praiseworthy"
  34,7,"The disbelievers say ňĻmockingly to one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúShall we show you a man who claims that when you have been utterly disintegrated you will be raised as a new creation"
  34,8,"Has he fabricated a lie against God or is he insane?‚ÄĚ In fact, those who do not believe in the Hereafter are bound for torment and have strayed farthest ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  34,9,"Have they not then seen all that surrounds them of the heavens and the earth? If We willed, We could cause the earth to swallow them up, or cause ňĻdeadlyňļ pieces of the sky to fall upon them. Surely in this is a sign for every servant who turns ňĻto Godňļ"
  34,10,"Indeed, We granted David a ňĻgreatňļ privilege from Us, ňĻcommanding:ňļ ‚ÄúO mountains! Echo his hymns! And the birds as well.‚ÄĚ We made iron mouldable for him"
  34,11,"instructing: ‚ÄúMake full-length armour, ňĻperfectlyňļ balancing the links. And work righteousness ňĻO family of David!ňļ. Indeed, I am All-Seeing of what you do.‚ÄĚ"
  34,12,"And to Solomon ňĻWe subjectedňļ the wind: its morning stride was a month‚Äôs journey and so was its evening stride. And We caused a stream of molten copper to flow for him, and ňĻWe subjectedňļ some of the jinn to work under him by his Lord‚Äôs Will. And whoever of them deviated from Our command, We made them taste the torment of the blaze"
  34,13,"They made for him whatever he desired of sanctuaries, statues,¬†basins as large as reservoirs, and cooking pots fixed ňĻinto the groundňļ. ňĻWe ordered:ňļ ‚ÄúWork gratefully, O family of David!‚ÄĚ ňĻOnlyňļ a few of My servants are ňĻtrulyňļ grateful"
  34,14,"When We decreed Solomon‚Äôs death, nothing indicated to the ňĻsubjectedňļ jinn that he was dead except the termites eating away his staff.¬†So when he collapsed, the jinn realized that if they had ňĻreallyňļ known the unseen, they would not have remained in ňĻsuchňļ humiliating servitude"
  34,15,"Indeed, there was a sign for ňĻthe tribe ofňļ Sheba in their homeland: two orchards‚ÄĒone to the right and the other to the left. ňĻThey were told:ňļ ‚ÄúEat from the provision of your Lord, and be grateful to Him. ňĻYours isňļ a good land and a forgiving Lord.‚ÄĚ"
  34,16,"But they turned away. So We sent against them a devastating flood, and replaced their orchards with two others producing bitter fruit, fruitless bushes,¬†and a few ňĻsparseňļ thorny trees"
  34,17,This is how We rewarded them for their ingratitude. Would We ever punish ňĻanyone in such a wayňļ except the ungrateful
  34,18,"We had also placed between them and the cities¬†We showered with blessings ňĻmany smallňļ towns within sight of one another. And We set moderate travel distances in between, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúTravel between them by day and night safely.‚ÄĚ"
  34,19,"But they said, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Make ňĻthe distances ofňļ our journeys longer,‚ÄĚ wronging themselves.¬†So We reduced them to ňĻcautionaryňļ tales, and scattered them utterly. Surely in this are lessons for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  34,20,"Indeed, Ibl√ģs‚Äô assumption about them has come true,¬†so they ňĻallňļ follow him, except a group of ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  34,21,"He does not have any authority over them, but ňĻOur Will isňļ only to distinguish those who believe in the Hereafter from those who are in doubt about it. And your Lord is a ňĻvigilantňļ Keeper over all things.‚ÄĚ"
  34,22,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúCall upon those you claim ňĻto be divineňļ besides God. They do not possess ňĻevenňļ an atom‚Äôs weight either in the heavens or the earth, nor do they have any share in ňĻgoverningňļ them. Nor is any of them a helper to Him.‚ÄĚ"
  34,23,"No intercession will be of any benefit with Him, except by those granted permission by Him. ňĻAt last,ňļ when the dread ňĻof Judgment Dayňļ is relieved from their hearts ňĻbecause they are permitted to intercedeňļ, they will ňĻexcitedlyňļ ask ňĻthe angelsňļ, ‚ÄúWhat has your Lord ňĻjustňļ said?‚ÄĚ The angels will reply, ‚ÄúThe truth! And He is the Most High, All-Great.‚ÄĚ"
  34,24,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho provides for you from the heavens and the earth?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúGod! Now, certainly one of our two groups¬†is ňĻrightlyňļ guided; the other is clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
  34,25,"Say, ‚ÄúYou will not be accountable for our misdeeds, nor will we be accountable for your deeds.‚ÄĚ"
  34,26,"Say, ‚ÄúOur Lord will gather us together, then He will judge between us with the truth. For He is the All-Knowing Judge.‚ÄĚ"
  34,27,"Say, ‚ÄúShow me those ňĻidolsňļ you have joined with Him as partners. No! In fact, He ňĻaloneňļ is God‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  34,28,"We have sent you ňĻO Prophetňļ only as a deliverer of good news and a warner to all of humanity, but most people do not know"
  34,29,"And they ask ňĻthe believersňļ, ‚ÄúWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  34,30,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúA Day has ňĻalreadyňļ been appointed for you, which you can neither delay nor advance by a ňĻsingleňļ moment.‚ÄĚ"
  34,31,"The disbelievers vow, ‚ÄúWe will never believe in this Quran, nor in those ňĻScripturesňļ before it.‚ÄĚ If only you could see when the wrongdoers will be detained before their Lord, throwing blame at each other! The lowly ňĻfollowersňļ will say to the arrogant ňĻleadersňļ, ‚ÄúHad it not been for you, we would certainly have been believers.‚ÄĚ"
  34,32,"The arrogant will respond to the lowly, ‚ÄúDid we ever hinder you from guidance after it came to you? In fact, you were wicked ňĻon your ownňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  34,33,"The lowly will say to the arrogant, ‚ÄúNo! It was your plotting by day and night‚ÄĒwhen you ordered us to disbelieve in God and to set up equals with Him.‚ÄĚ They will ňĻallňļ hide ňĻtheirňļ remorse when they see the torment. And We will put shackles around the necks of the disbelievers. Will they be rewarded except for what they used to do"
  34,34,"Whenever We sent a warner to a society, its elite would say, ‚ÄúWe truly reject what you have been sent with.‚ÄĚ"
  34,35,"Adding, ‚ÄúWe are far superior ňĻto the believersňļ in wealth and children, and we will never be punished.‚ÄĚ"
  34,36,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSurely ňĻit isňļ my Lord ňĻWhoňļ gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills. But most people do not know.‚ÄĚ"
  34,37,"It is not your wealth or children that bring you closer to Us. But those who believe and do good‚ÄĒit is they who will have a multiplied reward for what they did, and they will be secure in ňĻelevatedňļ mansions"
  34,38,"As for those who strive to discredit Our revelations, it is they who will be confined in punishment"
  34,39,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSurely ňĻit isňļ my Lord ňĻWhoňļ gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. And whatever you spend in charity, He will compensate ňĻyouňļ for it. For He is the Best Provider.‚ÄĚ"
  34,40,"And ňĻconsiderňļ the Day He will gather them all together, and then ask the angels, ‚ÄúWas it you that these ňĻpolytheistsňļ used to worship?‚ÄĚ"
  34,41,"They will say, ‚ÄúGlory be to You! Our loyalty is to You, not them. In fact, they ňĻonlyňļ followed the ňĻtemptations of evilňļ jinn,¬†in whom most of them had faith.‚ÄĚ"
  34,42,"So Today neither of you can benefit or protect each other. And We will say to the wrongdoers, ‚ÄúTaste the torment of the Fire, which you used to deny.‚ÄĚ"
  34,43,"When Our clear revelations are recited to them, they say, ‚ÄúThis is only a man who wishes to hinder you from what your forefathers used to worship.‚ÄĚ They also say, ‚ÄúThis ňĻQuranňļ is no more than a fabricated lie.‚ÄĚ And the disbelievers say of the truth when it has come to them, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  34,44,"ňĻThey say so even thoughňļ We had never given them any scriptures to study, nor did We ever send them a warner before you ňĻO Prophetňļ"
  34,45,"Those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them denied as well‚ÄĒand these ňĻMeccansňļ have not attained even one-tenth of what We had given their predecessors.¬†Yet ňĻwhenňļ they denied My messengers, how severe was My response"
  34,46,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI advise you to do ňĻonlyňļ one thing: stand up for ňĻthe sake ofňļ God‚ÄĒindividually or in pairs‚ÄĒthen reflect. Your fellow man¬†is not insane. He is only a warner to you before ňĻthe coming ofňļ a severe punishment.‚ÄĚ"
  34,47,"Say, ‚ÄúIf I had ever asked you for a reward, you could keep it. My reward is only from God. And He is a Witness over all things.‚ÄĚ"
  34,48,"Say, ‚ÄúSurely my Lord hurls the truth ňĻagainst falsehoodňļ. ňĻHe isňļ the Knower of all unseen.‚ÄĚ"
  34,49,"Say, ‚ÄúThe truth has come, and falsehood will vanish, never to return.‚ÄĚ"
  34,50,"Say, ‚ÄúIf I am astray, the loss is only mine. And if I am guided, it is ňĻonlyňļ because of what my Lord reveals to me. He is indeed All-Hearing, Ever Near.‚ÄĚ"
  34,51,If only you could see when they will be horrified with no escape ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ! And they will be seized from a nearby place
  34,52,"They will ňĻthenňļ cry, ‚ÄúWe do ňĻnowňļ believe in it ňĻallňļ.‚ÄĚ But how could they ňĻpossiblyňļ attain faith from a place so far-off ňĻfrom the worldňļ"
  34,53,"while they had already rejected it before, guessing blindly from a place ňĻequallyňļ far-away ňĻfrom the Hereafterňļ"
  34,54,"They will be sealed off from whatever they desire, as was done to their counterparts before. Indeed, they were ňĻallňļ in alarming doubt"
  35,1,"All praise is for God, the Originator of the heavens and the earth, Who made angels ňĻas Hisňļ messengers with wings‚ÄĒtwo, three, or four. He increases in creation whatever He wills. Surely God is Most Capable of everything"
  35,2,"Whatever mercy God opens up for people, none can withhold it. And whatever He withholds, none but Him can release it. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  35,3,O humanity! Remember God‚Äôs favours upon you. Is there any creator other than God who provides for you from the heavens and the earth? There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. How can you then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ
  35,4,"If you are rejected by them, so too were messengers before you. And to God ňĻallňļ matters will be returned ňĻfor judgmentňļ"
  35,5,"O humanity! Indeed, God‚Äôs promise is true. So do not let the life of this world deceive you, nor let the Chief Deceiver¬†deceive you about God"
  35,6,"Surely Satan is an enemy to you, so take him as an enemy. He only invites his followers to become inmates of the Blaze"
  35,7,Those who disbelieve will have a severe punishment. But those who believe and do good will have forgiveness and a great reward
  35,8,"Are those whose evil-doing is made so appealing to them that they deem it good ňĻlike those who are rightly guidedňļ? ňĻIt isňļ certainly God ňĻWhoňļ leaves to stray whoever He wills, and guides whoever He wills. So do not grieve yourself to death over them ňĻO Prophetňļ. Surely God is All-Knowing of what they do"
  35,9,"And it is God Who sends the winds, which then stir up ňĻvapour, formingňļ clouds, and then We drive them to a lifeless land, giving life to the earth after its death. Similar is the Resurrection"
  35,10,"Whoever seeks honour and power, then ňĻlet them know thatňļ all honour and power belongs to God. To Him ňĻaloneňļ good words ascend, and righteous deeds are raised up by Him. As for those who plot evil, they will suffer a severe punishment. And the plotting of such ňĻpeopleňļ is doomed ňĻto failňļ"
  35,11,"And ňĻit isňļ God ňĻWhoňļ created you from dust,¬†then ňĻdeveloped youňļ from a sperm-drop, then made you into pairs.¬†No female ever conceives or delivers without His knowledge. And no one‚Äôs life is made long or cut short but is ňĻwrittenňļ in a Record.¬†That is certainly easy for God"
  35,12,"The two bodies of water are not alike: one is fresh, palatable, and pleasant to drink and the other is salty and bitter. Yet from them both you eat tender seafood and extract ornaments to wear. And you see the ships ploughing their way through both, so you may seek His bounty and give thanks ňĻto Himňļ"
  35,13,"He merges the night into the day and the day into the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. That is God‚ÄĒyour Lord! All authority belongs to Him. But those ňĻidolsňļ you invoke besides Him do not possess even the skin of a date stone"
  35,14,"If you call upon them, they cannot hear your calls. And if they were to hear, they could not respond to you. On the Day of Judgment they will disown your worship ňĻof themňļ. And no one can inform you ňĻO Prophetňļ like the All-Knowledgeable"
  35,15,"O humanity! It is you who stand in need of God, but God ňĻaloneňļ is the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  35,16,"If He willed, He could eliminate you and produce a new creation"
  35,17,And that is not difficult for God ňĻat allňļ
  35,18,"No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. And if a sin-burdened soul cries for help with its burden, none of it will be carried‚ÄĒeven by a close relative. You ňĻO Prophetňļ can only warn those who stand in awe of their Lord without seeing Him¬†and establish prayer. Whoever purifies themselves, they only do so for their own good. And to God is the final return"
  35,19,Those blind ňĻto the truthňļ and those who can see are not equal
  35,20,nor are the darkness and the light
  35,21,nor the ňĻscorchingňļ heat and the ňĻcoolňļ shade
  35,22,"Nor are the dead and the living equal. Indeed, God ňĻaloneňļ makes whoever He wills hear, but you ňĻO Prophetňļ can never make those in the graves hear ňĻyour callňļ"
  35,23,You are only a warner
  35,24,We have surely sent you with the truth as a deliverer of good news and a warner. There is no community that has not had a warner
  35,25,"If they deny you, so did those before them. Their messengers came to them with clear proofs, divine Books, and enlightening Scriptures"
  35,26,Then I seized those who persisted in disbelief. How severe was My response
  35,27,"Do you not see that God sends down rain from the sky with which We bring forth fruits of different colours? And in the mountains are streaks of varying shades of white, red, and raven black"
  35,28,"just as people, living beings, and cattle are of various colours as well. Of all of God‚Äôs servants, only the knowledgeable ňĻof His mightňļ are ňĻtrulyňļ in awe of Him. God is indeed Almighty, All-Forgiving"
  35,29,"Surely those who recite the Book of God, establish prayer, and donate from what We have provided for them‚ÄĒsecretly and openly‚ÄĒňĻcanňļ hope for an exchange that will never fail"
  35,30,"so that He will reward them in full and increase them out of His grace. He is truly All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  35,31,"The Book We have revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ is the truth, confirming what came before it.¬†Surely God is All-Aware, All-Seeing of His servants"
  35,32,"Then We granted the Book to those We have chosen from Our servants. Some of them wrong themselves, some follow a middle course, and some are foremost in good deeds by God‚Äôs Will. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the greatest bounty"
  35,33,"They will enter the Gardens of Eternity, where they will be adorned with bracelets of gold and pearls, and their clothing will be silk"
  35,34,"And they will say, ‚ÄúPraise be to God, Who has kept away from us all ňĻcauses ofňļ sorrow. Our Lord is indeed All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  35,35,"ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who‚ÄĒout of His grace‚ÄĒhas settled us in the Home of Everlasting Stay, where we will be touched by neither fatigue nor weariness.‚ÄĚ"
  35,36,"As for the disbelievers, they will have the Fire of Hell, where they will not be ňĻallowed to beňļ finished by death, nor will its torment be lightened for them. This is how We reward every ňĻstubbornňļ disbeliever"
  35,37,"There they will be ňĻferventlyňļ screaming, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Take us out ňĻand send us backňļ. We will do good, unlike what we used to do.‚ÄĚ ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúDid We not give you lives long enough so that whoever wanted to be mindful could have done so? And the warner came to you. So taste ňĻthe punishmentňļ, for the wrongdoers have no helper.‚ÄĚ"
  35,38,"Indeed, God is the Knower of the unseen of the heavens and the earth. He surely knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  35,39,"He is the One Who has placed you as successors on earth. So whoever disbelieves will bear ňĻthe burden ofňļ their own disbelief. The disbelievers‚Äô denial only increases them in contempt in the sight of their Lord, and it will only contribute to their loss"
  35,40,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúHave you considered your associate-gods which you invoke besides God? Show me what they have created on earth! Or do they have a share in ňĻthe creation ofňļ the heavens? Or have We given the polytheists a Book, which serves as a clear proof for them? In fact, the wrongdoers promise each other nothing but delusion.‚ÄĚ"
  35,41,"Indeed, God ňĻaloneňļ keeps the heavens and the earth from falling apart. If they were to fall apart, none but Him could hold them up. He is truly Most Forbearing, All-Forgiving"
  35,42,"They swore by God their most solemn oaths that if a warner were to come to them, they would certainly be better guided than any other community. Yet when a warner did come to them, it only drove them farther away‚ÄĒ"
  35,43,"behaving arrogantly in the land and plotting evil. But evil plotting only backfires on those who plot. Are they awaiting anything but the fate of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before? You will find no change in the way of God, nor will you find it diverted ňĻto someone elseňļ"
  35,44,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them? They were far superior in might. But there is nothing that can escape God in the heavens or the earth. He is certainly All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  35,45,"If God were to punish people ňĻimmediatelyňļ for what they have committed, He would not have left a single living being on earth. But He delays them for an appointed term. And when their time arrives, then surely God is All-Seeing of His servants"
  36,1,Y√Ę-Sń©n
  36,2,"By the Quran, rich in wisdom"
  36,3,You ňĻO Prophetňļ are truly one of the messengers
  36,4,upon the Straight Path
  36,5,"ňĻThis isňļ a revelation from the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  36,6,"so that you may warn a people whose forefathers were not warned, and so are heedless"
  36,7,"The decree ňĻof tormentňļ has already been justified against most of them, for they will never believe"
  36,8,"ňĻIt is as ifňļ We have put shackles around their necks up to their chins, so their heads are forced up"
  36,9,"and have placed a barrier before them and a barrier behind them and covered them ňĻallňļ up, so they fail to see ňĻthe truthňļ"
  36,10,It is the same whether you warn them or not‚ÄĒthey will never believe
  36,11,You can only warn those who follow the Reminder¬†and are in awe of the Most Compassionate without seeing Him.¬†So give them good news of forgiveness and an honourable reward
  36,12,"It is certainly We Who resurrect the dead, and write what they send forth and what they leave behind. Everything is listed by Us in a perfect Record"
  36,13,"Give them an example ňĻO Prophetňļ of the residents of a town, when the messengers came to them"
  36,14,"We sent them two messengers, but they rejected both. So We reinforced ňĻthe twoňļ with a third, and they declared, ‚ÄúWe have indeed been sent to you ňĻas messengersňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  36,15,"The people replied, ‚ÄúYou are only humans like us, and the Most Compassionate has not revealed anything. You are simply lying!‚ÄĚ"
  36,16,"The messengers responded, ‚ÄúOur Lord knows that we have truly been sent to you"
  36,17,And our duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ clearly.‚ÄĚ
  36,18,"The people replied, ‚ÄúWe definitely see you as a bad omen for us. If you do not desist, we will certainly stone you ňĻto deathňļ and you will be touched with a painful punishment from us.‚ÄĚ"
  36,19,"The messengers said, ‚ÄúYour bad omen lies within yourselves. Are you saying this because you are reminded ňĻof the truthňļ? In fact, you are a transgressing people.‚ÄĚ"
  36,20,"Then from the farthest end of the city a man came, rushing. He advised, ‚ÄúO my people! Follow the messengers"
  36,21,"Follow those who ask no reward of you, and are ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  36,22,"And why should I not worship the One Who has originated me, and to Whom you will be returned"
  36,23,"How could I take besides Him other gods whose intercession would not be of any benefit to me, nor could they save me if the Most Compassionate intended to harm me"
  36,24,"Indeed, I would then be clearly astray"
  36,25,"I do believe in your Lord, so listen to me.‚ÄĚ"
  36,26,"ňĻBut they killed him, thenňļ he was told ňĻby the angelsňļ, ‚ÄúEnter Paradise!‚ÄĚ He said, ‚ÄúIf only my people knew"
  36,27,"of how my Lord has forgiven me, and made me one of the honourable.‚ÄĚ"
  36,28,"We did not send any soldiers from the heavens against his people after his death, nor did We need to"
  36,29,"All it took was one ňĻmightyňļ blast, and they were extinguished at once"
  36,30,"Oh pity, such beings! No messenger ever came to them without being mocked"
  36,31,Have the deniers not considered how many peoples We destroyed before them who never came back to life again
  36,32,Yet they will all be brought before Us
  36,33,"There is a sign for them in the dead earth: We give it life, producing grain from it for them to eat"
  36,34,"And We have placed in it gardens of palm trees and grapevines, and caused springs to gush forth in it"
  36,35,"so that they may eat from its fruit, which they had no hand in making. Will they not then give thanks"
  36,36,"Glory be to the One Who created all ňĻthings inňļ pairs‚ÄĒňĻbe itňļ what the earth produces, their genders, or what they do not know"
  36,37,"There is also a sign for them in the night: We strip from it daylight, then‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒthey are in darkness"
  36,38,"The sun travels for its fixed term. That is the design of the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  36,39,"As for the moon, We have ordained ňĻpreciseňļ phases for it, until it ends up like an old, curved palm stalk"
  36,40,"It is not for the sun to catch up with the moon,¬†nor does the night outrun the day. Each is travelling in an orbit of their own"
  36,41,Another sign for them is that We carried their ancestors ňĻwith Noahňļ in the fully loaded Ark
  36,42,and created for them similar things to ride in
  36,43,"If We willed, We could drown them: then no one would respond to their cries, nor would they be rescued‚ÄĒ"
  36,44,"except by mercy from Us, allowing them enjoyment for a ňĻlittleňļ while"
  36,45,"ňĻStill they turn awayňļ when it is said to them, ‚ÄúBeware of what is ahead of you ňĻin the Hereafterňļ and what is behind you ňĻof destroyed nationsňļ so you may be shown mercy.‚ÄĚ"
  36,46,"Whenever a sign comes to them from their Lord, they turn away from it"
  36,47,"And when it is said to them, ‚ÄúDonate from what God has provided for you,‚ÄĚ the disbelievers say to the believers, ‚ÄúWhy should we feed those whom God could have fed if He wanted to? You are clearly astray!‚ÄĚ"
  36,48,"And they ask ňĻthe believersňļ, ‚ÄúWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  36,49,"They must be awaiting a single Blast,¬†which will seize them while they are ňĻentrenchedňļ in ňĻworldlyňļ disputes"
  36,50,"Then they will not be able to make a ňĻlastňļ will, nor can they return to their own people"
  36,51,"The Trumpet will be blown ňĻa second timeňļ, then‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒthey will rush from the graves to their Lord"
  36,52,"They will cry, ‚ÄúWoe to us! Who has raised us up from our place of rest? This must be what the Most Compassionate warned us of; the messengers told the truth!‚ÄĚ"
  36,53,"It will only take one Blast, then at once they will all be brought before Us"
  36,54,"On that Day no soul will be wronged in the least, nor will you be rewarded except for what you used to do"
  36,55,"Indeed, on that Day the residents of Paradise will be busy enjoying themselves"
  36,56,"They and their spouses will be in ňĻcoolňļ shade, reclining on ňĻcanopiedňļ couches"
  36,57,There they will have fruits and whatever they desire
  36,58,And ‚ÄúPeace!‚ÄĚ will be ňĻtheirňļ greeting from the Merciful Lord
  36,59,"ňĻThen the disbelievers will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúStep away ňĻfrom the believersňļ this Day, O wicked ones"
  36,60,"Did I not command you, O Children of Adam, not to follow Satan, for he is truly your sworn enemy"
  36,61,but to worship Me ňĻaloneňļ? This is the Straight Path
  36,62,Yet he already misled great multitudes of you. Did you not have any sense
  36,63,This is the Hell you were warned of
  36,64,Burn in it Today for your disbelief.‚ÄĚ
  36,65,"On this Day We will seal their mouths, their hands will speak to Us, and their feet will testify to what they used to commit"
  36,66,"Had We willed, We could have easily blinded their eyes, so they would struggle to find their way. How then could they see"
  36,67,"And had We willed, We could have transfigured them on the spot,¬†so they could neither progress forward nor turn back"
  36,68,"And whoever We grant a long life, We reverse them in development.¬†Will they not then understand"
  36,69,"We have not taught him poetry, nor is it fitting for him. This ňĻBookňļ is only a Reminder and a clear Quran"
  36,70,to warn whoever is ňĻtrulyňļ alive and fulfil the decree ňĻof tormentňļ against the disbelievers
  36,71,"Do they not see that We singlehandedly¬†created for them, among other things, cattle which are under their control"
  36,72,"And We have subjected these ňĻanimalsňļ to them, so they may ride some and eat others"
  36,73,And they derive from them other benefits and drinks. Will they not then give thanks
  36,74,"Still they have taken other gods besides God, hoping to be helped ňĻby themňļ"
  36,75,"They cannot help the pagans, even though they serve the idols as dedicated guards"
  36,76,"So do not let their words grieve you ňĻO Prophetňļ. Indeed, We ňĻfullyňļ know what they conceal and what they reveal"
  36,77,"Do people not see that We have created them from a sperm-drop, then‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒthey openly challenge ňĻUsňļ"
  36,78,"And they argue with Us‚ÄĒforgetting they were created‚ÄĒsaying, ‚ÄúWho will give life to decayed bones?‚ÄĚ"
  36,79,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúThey will be revived by the One Who produced them the first time, for He has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of every created being"
  36,80,"ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who gives you fire from green trees, and‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒyou kindle ňĻfireňļ from them"
  36,81,"Can the One Who created the heavens and the earth not ňĻeasilyňļ resurrect these ňĻdeniersňļ?‚ÄĚ Yes ňĻHe canňļ! For He is the Master Creator, All-Knowing"
  36,82,"All it takes, when He wills something ňĻto beňļ, is simply to say to it: ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And it is"
  36,83,"So glory be to the One in Whose Hands is the authority over all things, and to Whom ňĻaloneňļ you will ňĻallňļ be returned"